271
00:17:45.787 --> 00:17:47.831
Take me. gravity!

272
00:17:50.750 --> 00:17:52.043
Um...

273
00:17:52.127 --> 00:17:53.378
Ouch!

274
00:17:53.461 --> 00:17:55.088
This is normal! Stay focused!

275
00:17:59.342 --> 00:18:00.552
Don't move. don't move. don't move!

276
00:18:05.598 --> 00:18:07.976
He's dead. I killed him!

277
00:18:08.518 --> 00:18:10.145
Whoo-hoo!

278
00:18:10.228 --> 00:18:11.938
- Wait. That was good?
- Oh. my...

279
00:18:12.021 --> 00:18:14.107
Did you see the height I got?

280
00:18:14.274 --> 00:18:15.859
Hey. nice ramping.

281
00:18:16.025 --> 00:18:17.527
Come on. let's build another one.

282
00:18:33.126 --> 00:18:34.210
Yahoo!

283
00:18:36.463 --> 00:18:38.006
Huh? Huh?

284
00:18:38.757 --> 00:18:40.133
Ow.

285
00:18:42.093 --> 00:18:43.261
Ha-ha!

286
00:18:48.057 --> 00:18:49.434
Whoo-hoo!

287
00:18:50.643 --> 00:18:52.312
Come on. Luca!

288
00:18:54.355 --> 00:18:56.357
Whoa!

289
00:19:13.166 --> 00:19:14.292
Huh.

290
00:19:21.424 --> 00:19:23.968
What's wrong with you. <i>stupido?</i>

291
00:19:25.637 --> 00:19:28.097
What's wrong with you. <i>stupido?</i>

292
00:19:39.859 --> 00:19:41.444
Look. we gotta ride together.

293
00:19:41.528 --> 00:19:43.321
If you don't sit on the back
and hold on to the front.

294
00:19:43.404 --> 00:19:44.823
the whole thing falls apart.

295
00:19:44.906 --> 00:19:47.325
Oh. And who's holding the ramp?

296
00:19:47.700 --> 00:19:50.161
The turtle. Come on.
He's faster than he looks.

297
00:19:50.245 --> 00:19:52.664
Oh. okay. Here we go.

298
00:19:54.249 --> 00:19:55.792
You. uh. coming?

299
00:19:55.875 --> 00:19:58.253
Nope. I can't do it.
Never in a million years.

300
00:19:58.336 --> 00:20:00.171
Hey. hey. hey. I know your problem.

301
00:20:00.255 --> 00:20:01.506
You've got a Bruno in your head.

302
00:20:01.923 --> 00:20:03.216
- A Bruno?
- Yeah.

303
00:20:03.299 --> 00:20:04.467
I get one. too. sometimes.

304
00:20:04.551 --> 00:20:07.011
"Alberto. you can't."
"Alberto. you're gonna die."

305
00:20:07.095 --> 00:20:08.930
"Alberto. don't put that in your mouth."

306
00:20:09.097 --> 00:20:12.100
Luca. it's simple.
Don't listen to stupid Bruno.

307
00:20:13.309 --> 00:20:14.686
Why is his name Bruno?

308
00:20:14.769 --> 00:20:15.770
I don't care. It doesn't matter.

309
00:20:15.854 --> 00:20:16.938
Call him whatever you want.

310
00:20:17.021 --> 00:20:19.440
Shut him up. Say. <i>"Silenzio. Bruno."</i>

311
00:20:22.068 --> 00:20:23.194
<i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

312
00:20:23.278 --> 00:20:25.488
Louder!<i>"Silenzio. Bruno!"</i>

313
00:20:25.572 --> 00:20:27.699
<i>- Silenzio. Bruno.
- "Silenzio. Bruno!"</i>

314
00:20:27.782 --> 00:20:28.783
<i>Silenzio. Bruno!</i>

315
00:20:28.867 --> 00:20:31.369
- Can you still hear him?
- Nope! Just you!

316
00:20:31.452 --> 00:20:33.538
Good! Now. hang on!

317
00:20:35.748 --> 00:20:37.292
<i>Andiamo!</i>

318
00:20:41.588 --> 00:20:43.548
Yeah!

319
00:20:46.676 --> 00:20:48.052
<i>Silenzio. Bruno. Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

320
00:20:48.136 --> 00:20:49.137
<i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

321
00:20:49.220 --> 00:20:50.930
<i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

322
00:21:00.690 --> 00:21:02.609
- Whoa.
- Wow.

323
00:21:02.692 --> 00:21:03.693
Uh-oh.

324
00:21:12.577 --> 00:21:14.621
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

325
00:21:14.704 --> 00:21:17.582
Yes! We're alive! I can't believe it!

326
00:21:17.665 --> 00:21:19.250
- Take that. Bruno!
- Yes!

327
00:21:23.212 --> 00:21:25.465
What are all those tiny lights?

328
00:21:25.798 --> 00:21:27.967
Anchovies. They go there to sleep.

329
00:21:29.719 --> 00:21:30.929
- Really?
- Yeah.

330
00:21:31.095 --> 00:21:33.056
And the big fish protects them.

331
00:21:33.139 --> 00:21:34.140
I touched it once.

332
00:21:34.974 --> 00:21:36.184
I don't know. it felt like a fish.

333
00:21:36.267 --> 00:21:37.268
Wow.

334
00:21:37.352 --> 00:21:39.729
Your life is so much cooler than mine.

335
00:21:39.812 --> 00:21:41.064
I never go anywhere.

336
00:21:41.689 --> 00:21:43.316
I just dream about it.

337
00:21:43.566 --> 00:21:44.734
You came up here.

338
00:21:44.901 --> 00:21:45.985
Thanks to you.

339
00:21:46.653 --> 00:21:49.072
Otherwise. I never would've
seen any of this.

340
00:21:53.284 --> 00:21:54.994
Have you ever gone to the human town?

341
00:21:55.078 --> 00:21:56.079
Yeah!

342
00:21:56.162 --> 00:21:57.580
Uh... No.

343
00:21:57.664 --> 00:21:59.999
But. but my dad told me all about it.

344
00:22:00.083 --> 00:22:01.626
So. I'm pretty much an expert.

345
00:22:02.627 --> 00:22:04.337
Your dad sounds so cool.

346
00:22:04.545 --> 00:22:06.422
You're lucky he lets you do what you want.

347
00:22:06.839 --> 00:22:07.924
Yeah. For sure.

348
00:22:11.844 --> 00:22:13.846
Hey. you remember that time
we almost hit that rock?

349
00:22:13.930 --> 00:22:15.306
And we flew through the air.

350
00:22:15.390 --> 00:22:18.393
and I was like. "Yeah!"
And then you were like. "No!"

351
00:22:20.937 --> 00:22:23.523
Wouldn't it be amazing
to have a real Vespa?

352
00:22:23.606 --> 00:22:26.609
Yeah. That's the dream.

353
00:22:27.235 --> 00:22:28.361
Yeah.

354
00:22:34.450 --> 00:22:35.576
Whoo!

355
00:22:37.203 --> 00:22:38.955
Oh. Luca. look!

356
00:22:40.123 --> 00:22:41.708
Whoa!

357
00:22:41.791 --> 00:22:43.626
Wild Vespas!

358
00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:45.628
Whoo-hoo!

359
00:22:46.671 --> 00:22:47.964
Luca. take over!

360
00:22:49.090 --> 00:22:51.217
Yeah. man!

361
00:22:54.637 --> 00:22:55.722
Come on. faster!

362
00:22:57.098 --> 00:23:00.101
Yeah! Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

363
00:23:00.184 --> 00:23:02.562
Whoo-hoo!

364
00:23:10.528 --> 00:23:12.321
Whoa.

365
00:23:16.701 --> 00:23:19.245
I'm doing it. Alberto! I'm doing it!

366
00:23:19.871 --> 00:23:20.872
Alberto?

367
00:23:27.837 --> 00:23:30.590
Oh. no! I fell asleep!

368
00:23:30.757 --> 00:23:31.758
What?

369
00:23:35.803 --> 00:23:36.846
Phew.

370
00:23:41.809 --> 00:23:42.810
Uh...

371
00:23:43.603 --> 00:23:46.397
Daniela. do we really need
to go through with this?

372
00:23:46.481 --> 00:23:47.607
With what?

373
00:23:47.690 --> 00:23:50.860
Uh. son. you're in big trouble.

374
00:23:50.943 --> 00:23:52.612
You need to promise us

375
00:23:52.695 --> 00:23:56.365
that you'll never sneak off
to the surface again.

376
00:23:56.449 --> 00:23:58.034
Uh. I'm really sorry.

377
00:23:58.117 --> 00:24:01.370
But. you know. it's not
that dangerous up there.

378
00:24:01.454 --> 00:24:02.580
Maybe I could show you.

379
00:24:02.663 --> 00:24:05.249
I told you. Our son has a death wish.

380
00:24:05.333 --> 00:24:07.001
But. Mom. we're always careful!

381
00:24:07.085 --> 00:24:08.086
"We"?

382
00:24:09.045 --> 00:24:11.631
Me and my friend. Alberto.

383
00:24:12.006 --> 00:24:14.092
But it's okay. He's one of us.

384
00:24:14.175 --> 00:24:17.887
Ah. yes. There's usually a bad influence.

385
00:24:18.262 --> 00:24:21.224
Good thing you sent for me
when you did. huh?

386
00:24:21.724 --> 00:24:25.311
Luca. this is my brother. your Uncle Ugo.

387
00:24:25.394 --> 00:24:27.230
Thanks again for coming all this way

388
00:24:27.313 --> 00:24:28.606
on such short notice.

389
00:24:29.482 --> 00:24:30.733
Of course.

390
00:24:30.817 --> 00:24:32.026
Hello. Luca.

391
00:24:32.110 --> 00:24:34.654
It's really nice to...

392
00:24:36.572 --> 00:24:38.449
Luca. I need you to punch his heart.

393
00:24:38.825 --> 00:24:40.827
That's right. The red thing. Punch it.

394
00:24:40.910 --> 00:24:42.328
- Harder!
- Oh.

395
00:24:44.122 --> 00:24:46.874
Thanks for that. Too much oxygen up here.

396
00:24:46.958 --> 00:24:50.586
Not like the deep.
As you'll learn.

397
00:24:51.295 --> 00:24:52.296
What?

398
00:24:52.380 --> 00:24:53.923
Sure. there's no sunlight.

399
00:24:54.006 --> 00:24:56.300
but there's nothing to see anyway.

400
00:24:56.384 --> 00:25:00.138
Or do. It's just you and your thoughts.

401
00:25:00.888 --> 00:25:04.100
and all the whale carcass you can eat.

402
00:25:04.308 --> 00:25:07.019
Little bits of it
just float into your mouth.

403
00:25:07.103 --> 00:25:08.271
You can't stop it.

404
00:25:08.354 --> 00:25:10.773
You can't see it. So if you...

405
00:25:10.857 --> 00:25:13.776
The mouth opened.
the whale carcass go in.

406
00:25:13.943 --> 00:25:16.070
Yes. good. I recommend it.

407
00:25:16.988 --> 00:25:18.573
Come on. No time to waste.

408
00:25:18.656 --> 00:25:20.408
Mom. what does he mean?

409
00:25:20.491 --> 00:25:22.451
You're going to stay with Uncle Ugo

410
00:25:22.535 --> 00:25:23.661
for the rest of the season.

411
00:25:23.744 --> 00:25:24.829
No. I can't!

412
00:25:24.912 --> 00:25:27.415
Two seasons. then. Wanna go for three?

413
00:25:27.498 --> 00:25:28.875
Why are you doing this?

414
00:25:28.958 --> 00:25:31.752
The world is a very dangerous place. Luca.

415
00:25:31.836 --> 00:25:34.255
and if I have to send you
to the bottom of the ocean

416
00:25:34.338 --> 00:25:35.965
to keep you safe. so be it.

417
00:25:36.048 --> 00:25:37.341
You don't know what it's like up there!

418
00:25:37.425 --> 00:25:40.511
I know you. And I know
what's best for you.

419
00:25:40.595 --> 00:25:42.221
It's done.

420
00:25:43.681 --> 00:25:46.142
Hey. Look me in the eye.

421
00:25:46.642 --> 00:25:48.811
You know I love you. right?

422
00:26:02.325 --> 00:26:04.160
They're sending me to the deep!

423
00:26:04.243 --> 00:26:05.870
To live with my weird see-through uncle!

424
00:26:05.953 --> 00:26:07.538
- What do I do?
- Stay?

425
00:26:07.622 --> 00:26:09.415
Up here? They'll come looking for me.

426
00:26:09.498 --> 00:26:11.042
Okay. that may be true.

427
00:26:11.667 --> 00:26:14.962
but will they come
looking for you over there?

428
00:26:16.130 --> 00:26:17.882
No way. That's crazy.

429
00:26:17.965 --> 00:26:20.468
I mean. that place must be full of Vespas.

430
00:26:20.551 --> 00:26:22.470
- There's gotta be one for us.
- Huh.

431
00:26:22.595 --> 00:26:24.138
A real Vespa.

432
00:26:24.513 --> 00:26:26.057
Could we even survive over there?

433
00:26:26.140 --> 00:26:28.893
You and me? We can do anything.

434
00:26:28.976 --> 00:26:30.645
We'd swim right over to Vespatown.

435
00:26:30.728 --> 00:26:31.812
track down <i>Signor</i> Vespa.

436
00:26:33.042 --> 00:26:34.251
Wait. Do you really think
there's a <i>Signor</i> Vespa?

437
00:26:34.335 --> 00:26:36.045
- Makes sense. right?
- Yes. Continue.

438
00:26:36.128 --> 00:26:40.049
And we say. <i>"Signor</i> Vespa.
build us one of these!"

439
00:26:40.132 --> 00:26:42.926
Whoa. This is the greatest
drawing I've ever seen.

440
00:26:43.010 --> 00:26:45.804
Yeah. I know. Luca. think about it.

441
00:26:46.055 --> 00:26:47.973
Every day. we'll ride someplace new.

442
00:26:48.057 --> 00:26:50.684
and every night.
we'll sleep under the fish.

443
00:26:51.483 --> 00:26:53.777
No one to tell us what to do.
Just you and me out there.

444
00:26:54.403 --> 00:26:55.404
<i>Free.</i>

445
00:26:55.487 --> 00:26:56.572
Whoo-hoo!

446
00:26:56.655 --> 00:26:58.532
Take me. gravity!

447
00:27:05.205 --> 00:27:06.457
<i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

448
00:27:07.332 --> 00:27:08.917
Whoo-hoo!

449
00:27:10.127 --> 00:27:11.211
Yeah!

450
00:27:21.764 --> 00:27:23.432
Come on!

451
00:27:24.725 --> 00:27:25.851
Ha-ha!

452
00:27:50.167 --> 00:27:52.044
Yeah! Whoo!

453
00:28:00.260 --> 00:28:01.345
Whoa.

454
00:28:03.972 --> 00:28:06.183
<i>Papà.</i> what's that?

455
00:28:08.519 --> 00:28:09.937
How do we get in?

456
00:28:23.283 --> 00:28:24.618
This will be a breeze.

457
00:28:24.701 --> 00:28:26.453
- Just don't get wet.
- Uh...

458
00:28:35.295 --> 00:28:37.172
Actually. this town seems
a little crowded.

459
00:28:37.256 --> 00:28:38.924
Hey! <i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

460
00:28:39.091 --> 00:28:40.801
What's wrong with you. <i>stupido?</i>

461
00:28:40.884 --> 00:28:41.885
Huh?

462
00:28:43.595 --> 00:28:44.888
- Huh! It worked.
- See?

463
00:28:45.222 --> 00:28:47.266
You just gotta follow my lead.

464
00:29:16.003 --> 00:29:18.213
Classic human town. Pretty cool. right?

465
00:29:18.297 --> 00:29:20.090
Hey. you do it now. Just say the thing.

466
00:29:21.008 --> 00:29:22.009
Mmm.

467
00:29:22.092 --> 00:29:23.677
Madams.

468
00:29:23.760 --> 00:29:25.512
what's wrong with you. <i>stupido?</i>

469
00:29:33.896 --> 00:29:35.314
Maybe I said it wrong?

470
00:29:35.397 --> 00:29:36.648
Mmm. Mmm!

471
00:29:40.068 --> 00:29:41.069
Wow!

472
00:29:41.612 --> 00:29:42.613
Mmm!

473
00:29:51.163 --> 00:29:53.624
Alberto. this is too dangerous.

474
00:29:53.790 --> 00:29:55.167
Let's get out of here.

475
00:29:55.626 --> 00:29:56.668
And go where?

476
00:30:01.757 --> 00:30:02.758
Whoa.

477
00:30:02.841 --> 00:30:04.009
It's <i>Signor</i> Vespa!

478
00:30:06.345 --> 00:30:08.055
<i>Mannaggia!</i> Here we go.

479
00:30:09.264 --> 00:30:11.892
Oh. <i>mamma mia!</i> Please. no more revving.

480
00:30:13.644 --> 00:30:15.145
<i>Ciao! Ciao!</i>

481
00:30:16.772 --> 00:30:18.732
Beep. beep!

482
00:30:18.815 --> 00:30:21.777
Pride of Portorosso coming through!

483
00:30:21.860 --> 00:30:23.362
<i>- Ciao. belle!</i>
- Hmm. blech!

484
00:30:23.445 --> 00:30:24.780
You're making me blush.

485
00:30:26.907 --> 00:30:30.827
And now. who wants to watch me
eat a big sandwich? Hmm?

486
00:30:32.371 --> 00:30:33.872
There it is.

487
00:30:33.956 --> 00:30:36.041
That's how we're gonna see the world.

488
00:30:36.124 --> 00:30:37.709
Hey. little help?

489
00:30:40.337 --> 00:30:41.338
- Huh?
- Hmm?

490
00:30:46.593 --> 00:30:48.845
Oh. <i>mamma mia!</i>
Talk to Ercole. Are you hurt?

491
00:30:48.929 --> 00:30:49.930
Well. my head kinda hurts...

492
00:30:50.013 --> 00:30:52.182
Not you. Ciccio! Out of the way!

493
00:30:52.391 --> 00:30:56.144
Oh. <i>piccolina.</i> if there is
so much as a scratch...

494
00:30:57.354 --> 00:30:59.815
Someone got lucky today. Hmm?

495
00:30:59.898 --> 00:31:01.108
Who got lucky?

496
00:31:03.360 --> 00:31:05.737
Mm-hmm. Out-of-towners. eh?

497
00:31:05.821 --> 00:31:07.406
Let me welcome you.

498
00:31:10.242 --> 00:31:11.284
Ciccio?

499
00:31:11.368 --> 00:31:14.538
I am delighted to meet you.
Number One and Number Two.

500
00:31:14.621 --> 00:31:16.623
I love your stylish clothes.

501
00:31:16.707 --> 00:31:19.626
Where did you get them?
A dead body?

502
00:31:19.710 --> 00:31:20.711
Dead body.

503
00:31:20.794 --> 00:31:21.795
I'm kidding.

504
00:31:21.878 --> 00:31:23.964
Uh... Look. <i>Signor</i> Vespa...

505
00:31:24.047 --> 00:31:26.299
<i>Signor</i> Vespa?

506
00:31:26.383 --> 00:31:27.592
This guy funny. hmm?

507
00:31:27.676 --> 00:31:29.136
I am Ercole Visconti.

508
00:31:29.219 --> 00:31:31.513
Five-time winner of the Portorosso Cup.

509
00:31:31.680 --> 00:31:33.181
The Portorosso what?

510
00:31:33.265 --> 00:31:34.558
The Portorosso Cup!

511
00:31:35.726 --> 00:31:38.395
How do you think
I paid for my beautiful Vespa?

512
00:31:40.564 --> 00:31:41.815
Hey. stop looking.

513
00:31:41.898 --> 00:31:42.899
She's too beautiful for you.

514
00:31:43.275 --> 00:31:45.652
I. uh...

515
00:31:45.736 --> 00:31:47.362
I love it.

516
00:31:47.446 --> 00:31:49.156
The little guy can't even get a word out.

517
00:31:49.239 --> 00:31:52.868
Oof. And he smells like behind
the <i>pescheria</i>.

518
00:31:52.951 --> 00:31:54.619
Hey. my friend smells amazing.

519
00:31:54.703 --> 00:31:57.039
Sorry. sorry. I'll make it up to him.

520
00:31:57.122 --> 00:31:58.999
Ciccio. Guido.

521
00:31:59.082 --> 00:32:00.083
What are you doing?

522
00:32:00.167 --> 00:32:01.168
- Luca!
- Alberto!

523
00:32:01.251 --> 00:32:02.377
Ah. just a little bath.

524
00:32:02.461 --> 00:32:03.795
- Oh. no. no. no!
- It's funny.

525
00:32:03.879 --> 00:32:05.380
Huh?

526
00:32:07.007 --> 00:32:08.425
- No!
- Huh?

527
00:32:08.508 --> 00:32:10.385
Hey! Ercole. <i>basta!</i>

528
00:32:10.761 --> 00:32:13.847
Oh. look who's here. Spewlia.

529
00:32:13.930 --> 00:32:16.099
Wow.
That's how you're training for the race?

530
00:32:17.267 --> 00:32:18.518
Your reign of terror is

531
00:32:18.602 --> 00:32:20.228
- coming to an end!
- "Coming to an end."

532
00:32:20.312 --> 00:32:21.480
You mean like a year ago?

533
00:32:21.563 --> 00:32:23.148
When you quit in the middle of the race?

534
00:32:23.231 --> 00:32:26.068
Because you couldn't stop
throwing up?

535
00:32:26.151 --> 00:32:28.403
I didn't quit. They made me stop.

536
00:32:28.737 --> 00:32:30.864
I think that is worse. Now. go away.

537
00:32:30.947 --> 00:32:32.324
I'm having fun with my new friends.

538
00:32:32.407 --> 00:32:33.408
They're coming with me.

539
00:32:34.284 --> 00:32:37.079
Hop on. I could use the extra weight.

540
00:32:39.067 --> 00:32:40.819
Fine. Go start a club. For losers!

541
00:32:41.987 --> 00:32:44.614
<i>Maggiore!</i> Another sighting.
In the harbor. this time.

542
00:32:44.698 --> 00:32:46.950
I know. We are setting up a reward.

543
00:32:47.034 --> 00:32:49.036
Someone's gonna win a nice prize.

544
00:32:49.119 --> 00:32:50.746
Me! Me! I win the prizes.

545
00:32:50.829 --> 00:32:51.830
Ciccio!

546
00:32:51.913 --> 00:32:52.956
Get your daddy's harpoon!

547
00:32:53.040 --> 00:32:54.750
We're gonna catch a sea monster.

548
00:32:54.833 --> 00:32:55.375
<i>Sì!</i>

549
00:32:56.400 --> 00:32:58.569
<i>Sto imbecille</i> thinks he can be a jerk

550
00:32:58.652 --> 00:32:59.653
'cause he keeps winning the race.

551
00:32:59.736 --> 00:33:01.238
which he shouldn't even
get to do anymore.

552
00:33:01.321 --> 00:33:03.448
'cause he's too old
and too much of a jerk!

553
00:33:04.783 --> 00:33:06.243
You know. we underdogs

554
00:33:06.326 --> 00:33:07.703
have to look out for each other. right?

555
00:33:08.203 --> 00:33:09.246
What's under the dogs?

556
00:33:09.705 --> 00:33:10.706
Underdogs.

557
00:33:10.789 --> 00:33:12.249
You know. kids who are different.

558
00:33:12.332 --> 00:33:13.333
dressed weird.

559
00:33:13.417 --> 00:33:15.627
or a little sweatier than average.

560
00:33:15.711 --> 00:33:16.795
Uh...

561
00:33:16.879 --> 00:33:18.463
Too much? Too much.

562
00:33:18.797 --> 00:33:20.841
So. are you in town for the race?

563
00:33:22.342 --> 00:33:23.760
The Portorosso Cup?

564
00:33:25.637 --> 00:33:27.181
Well. good talk.

565
00:33:27.472 --> 00:33:30.684
I gotta deliver these.
Always be training. you know?

566
00:33:32.060 --> 00:33:34.771
We should ask her
about this Portorosso Cup race.

567
00:33:34.855 --> 00:33:37.566
That's how the loud scary human said
he got his Vespa.

568
00:33:38.942 --> 00:33:39.943
Giulia!

569
00:33:40.027 --> 00:33:42.362
Oh!

570
00:33:42.446 --> 00:33:43.614
- Uh. <i>grazie.
- Ciao.</i>

571
00:33:43.697 --> 00:33:44.823
Hey. uh. Spewlia?

572
00:33:44.907 --> 00:33:47.034
Giulia. My name is Giulia.

573
00:33:47.492 --> 00:33:51.496
Okay. When you race in a cup.
what do you get?

574
00:33:52.247 --> 00:33:53.999
<i>Soldi</i>. Prize money.

575
00:33:54.333 --> 00:33:55.334
Oh.

576
00:33:55.417 --> 00:33:56.418
Okay.

577
00:33:56.501 --> 00:33:58.253
- No. no! Keep going!
- What? Why?

578
00:33:58.337 --> 00:33:59.338
Ask her about the prize money!

579
00:33:59.421 --> 00:34:00.464
But that stuff is useless.

580
00:34:00.547 --> 00:34:02.132
- Maybe that becomes a Vespa.
- How does that become...

581
00:34:02.216 --> 00:34:03.425
- Just ask her!
- Fine. fine. fine.

582
00:34:03.926 --> 00:34:05.636
- Hello again.
<i>- Ciao.</i>

583
00:34:05.719 --> 00:34:08.513
Can we turn the money into something else?

584
00:34:09.097 --> 00:34:10.849
- Something like...
- That.

585
00:34:12.017 --> 00:34:14.603
Pfft. No. But it could get you that.

586
00:34:28.103 --> 00:34:29.187
Whoo-hoo!

587
00:34:29.771 --> 00:34:30.772
It's so beautiful.

588
00:34:30.855 --> 00:34:32.190
Yes. we need it.

589
00:34:32.273 --> 00:34:33.983
Great. so we'll just win the race.

590
00:34:35.485 --> 00:34:36.694
You'll have to beat Ercole.

591
00:34:36.861 --> 00:34:38.238
Okay. so we'll beat Ercole.

592
00:34:38.321 --> 00:34:39.614
Huh. Really?

593
00:34:39.697 --> 00:34:41.658
Thinks he'll beat Ercole.
this guy.

594
00:34:41.741 --> 00:34:43.368
First of all. get in line!

595
00:34:43.451 --> 00:34:46.955
Every summer. that jerk
makes my life miserable.

596
00:34:47.038 --> 00:34:49.874
So. no one's taking him down
unless it's me!

597
00:34:50.917 --> 00:34:52.877
Second. this isn't any old race.

598
00:34:53.403 --> 00:34:56.198
It's an epic. grueling.
traditional Italian triathlon.

599
00:34:56.281 --> 00:34:59.117
Swimming. cycling. and eating pasta.

600
00:34:59.368 --> 00:35:00.410
So. you'd need a teammate.

601
00:35:00.494 --> 00:35:03.163
Well. we'll figure it out.
Thanks. human girl.

602
00:35:04.831 --> 00:35:07.501
Hey. hey. wait. Wait. Alberto.

603
00:35:08.001 --> 00:35:09.336
What if we join her team?

604
00:35:09.419 --> 00:35:10.462
<i>Grazie! Arrivederci!</i>

605
00:35:10.545 --> 00:35:12.172
Hmm. Better idea.

606
00:35:12.255 --> 00:35:13.757
Hey. Spew... Girl!

607
00:35:13.840 --> 00:35:14.925
<i>Santa mozzarella.</i>

608
00:35:15.008 --> 00:35:17.052
Congratulations. you're joining our team.

609
00:35:17.135 --> 00:35:19.012
I race alone.

610
00:35:24.267 --> 00:35:26.645
But we could be under the dogs. too.

611
00:35:26.728 --> 00:35:27.938
Hey. it's okay. Luca.

612
00:35:28.021 --> 00:35:30.399
She'd rather do
the whole race alone again.

613
00:35:30.482 --> 00:35:32.150
Maybe this time
she won't throw up as much.

614
00:35:32.234 --> 00:35:33.652
Uh. hang on.

615
00:35:36.196 --> 00:35:38.156
You wanna be on my team. eh?

616
00:35:38.448 --> 00:35:39.700
Let's see what you got.

617
00:35:45.414 --> 00:35:46.540
All right. try jumping onto it.

618
00:35:47.541 --> 00:35:48.542
No. no. no.

619
00:35:48.625 --> 00:35:50.252
You gotta show it you're the boss!

620
00:35:52.129 --> 00:35:53.672
<i>Santa mozzarella.</i>

621
00:35:53.755 --> 00:35:55.048
- Eyes up.
- Huh?

622
00:35:55.132 --> 00:35:57.300
Looking down is what's making you fall.

623
00:36:00.220 --> 00:36:01.221
Whoa.

624
00:36:03.473 --> 00:36:04.850
Whoa. I'm doing it.

625
00:36:06.226 --> 00:36:07.602
So. can we be on the team?

626
00:36:09.020 --> 00:36:10.105
Can you dodge obstacles?

627
00:36:10.188 --> 00:36:12.107
What if an old lady crosses your path?

628
00:36:13.525 --> 00:36:16.111
Can you withstand
passive-aggressive verbal assaults?

629
00:36:16.194 --> 00:36:18.155
"Nice bike.
Number One and Number Two.

630
00:36:18.238 --> 00:36:19.239
"I was kidding.

631
00:36:19.322 --> 00:36:20.782
"Your bike is a disgrace."

632
00:36:21.158 --> 00:36:22.242
Finally. can you handle

633
00:36:22.325 --> 00:36:24.536
the course's fiendishly difficult terrain?

634
00:36:24.619 --> 00:36:25.996
<i>Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

635
00:36:33.295 --> 00:36:34.296
Hmm.

636
00:36:36.548 --> 00:36:37.966
Stop. What about you?

637
00:36:38.049 --> 00:36:39.134
Can you swim at least?

638
00:36:39.217 --> 00:36:43.054
Yeah. I'm amazingly
bad at swimming.

639
00:36:43.138 --> 00:36:45.515
You can't swim.
you can barely ride a bike.

640
00:36:47.058 --> 00:36:48.852
I mean. where are you even from?

641
00:36:48.935 --> 00:36:50.353
We're not telling you our secrets!

642
00:36:50.437 --> 00:36:52.230
- We're runaways.
- Runaways?

643
00:36:52.314 --> 00:36:53.648
I don't know. <i>ragazzi...</i>

644
00:36:54.316 --> 00:36:55.317
Please?

645
00:36:55.609 --> 00:36:58.111
My family was gonna send me
somewhere horrible.

646
00:36:58.195 --> 00:37:00.030
Away from everything I love.

647
00:37:00.197 --> 00:37:02.574
But if we win this race. well.

648
00:37:02.657 --> 00:37:04.034
we can be free.

649
00:37:05.118 --> 00:37:07.162
My life's great. I'm just helping him out.

650
00:37:07.245 --> 00:37:08.371
Hmm.

651
00:37:08.455 --> 00:37:09.915
Just give me one more chance.

652
00:37:10.415 --> 00:37:11.416
No.

653
00:37:12.042 --> 00:37:13.752
You guys want it just as bad as I do.

654
00:37:13.835 --> 00:37:14.836
You have the hunger.

655
00:37:14.920 --> 00:37:16.129
That's the most important thing.

656
00:37:16.296 --> 00:37:17.631
I'm definitely hungry.

657
00:37:17.714 --> 00:37:20.509
<i>Perfetto!</i> You eat. you bike. and I swim.

658
00:37:20.592 --> 00:37:22.886
Underdogs?

659
00:37:23.845 --> 00:37:25.138
Underdogs.

660
00:37:25.555 --> 00:37:27.808
Now we just need money for the entry fee.

661
00:37:27.974 --> 00:37:29.267
From my dad.

662
00:37:38.735 --> 00:37:41.822
All right. just let me do the talking
and act casual.

663
00:37:41.905 --> 00:37:43.365
He doesn't do well with fear.

664
00:37:43.448 --> 00:37:44.908
Hey. <i>Papà!</i> I brought

665
00:37:44.991 --> 00:37:46.368
some friends for dinner.

666
00:37:46.451 --> 00:37:48.036
Is there enough for four?

667
00:37:50.831 --> 00:37:51.998
Whoa.

668
00:37:52.082 --> 00:37:53.834
What's wrong with you. <i>stu...</i>

669
00:38:01.508 --> 00:38:03.093
What do you think he kills with those?

670
00:38:04.056 --> 00:38:06.434
Anything that swims.

671
00:38:06.517 --> 00:38:08.227
<i>Hai visto il giornale</i> today?

672
00:38:08.311 --> 00:38:10.354
That photo is a fake. <i>Papà.</i>

673
00:38:11.022 --> 00:38:14.275
Everyone in Portorosso
pretends to believe in sea monsters.

674
00:38:14.775 --> 00:38:16.694
Huh.

675
00:38:16.777 --> 00:38:18.863
Well. I'm not pretending.

676
00:38:20.865 --> 00:38:22.074
Huh?

677
00:38:32.571 --> 00:38:33.905
Slipped.

678
00:38:35.657 --> 00:38:36.658
Eh.

679
00:38:38.076 --> 00:38:39.119
Phew!

680
00:38:42.038 --> 00:38:43.165
Dinner's ready.

681
00:38:43.582 --> 00:38:45.208
Trenette al pesto.

682
00:39:08.398 --> 00:39:09.483
Mmm!

683
00:39:13.445 --> 00:39:14.446
Uh...

684
00:39:15.113 --> 00:39:16.114
Mmm!

685
00:39:17.449 --> 00:39:18.325
Okay.

686
00:39:19.928 --> 00:39:22.388
Where did you boys say you were from?

687
00:39:24.265 --> 00:39:26.810
They're. uh.
classmates. From Genova.

688
00:39:26.893 --> 00:39:28.603
Luca and. uh...

689
00:39:28.686 --> 00:39:30.522
- Alberto.
- Alberto.

690
00:39:31.231 --> 00:39:33.733
And what brings you to Portorosso?

691
00:39:33.817 --> 00:39:34.901
Oh. Uh...

692
00:39:34.984 --> 00:39:36.277
Funny you should ask.

693
00:39:36.361 --> 00:39:37.570
They came for the race.

694
00:39:38.238 --> 00:39:39.322
The race?

695
00:39:39.489 --> 00:39:40.698
Yeah.

696
00:39:40.782 --> 00:39:43.409
Uh. you know what? Don't worry about it.

697
00:39:43.493 --> 00:39:45.161
"Don't worry about it"?

698
00:39:45.775 --> 00:39:47.777
Mm-hmm. Don't worry about it.

699
00:39:47.860 --> 00:39:51.030
Giulietta. A word.

700
00:39:52.823 --> 00:39:54.742
I don't want you doing the race again.

701
00:39:54.825 --> 00:39:55.993
You get so upset.

702
00:39:56.077 --> 00:39:58.537
<i>Papà. per favore.</i> I have a team now.

703
00:39:58.621 --> 00:40:01.624
There's also the entry fee.
Money is tight.

704
00:40:01.707 --> 00:40:03.834
I'll work double shifts at the <i>pescheria.</i>
Whatever you need.

705
00:40:03.918 --> 00:40:06.253
I can't sell what I don't have.

706
00:40:06.337 --> 00:40:08.673
What I need is more fish in my net.

707
00:40:11.050 --> 00:40:12.677
Um. excuse me?

708
00:40:12.760 --> 00:40:14.136
We could help.

709
00:40:14.220 --> 00:40:15.638
You know fish?

710
00:40:15.721 --> 00:40:17.556
Oh. we? We know lots of fish.

711
00:40:17.640 --> 00:40:19.809
- Huh.
- Can this face lose?

712
00:40:21.686 --> 00:40:24.522
You want to work? I'll put you to work.

713
00:40:24.605 --> 00:40:26.107
Really?

714
00:40:26.190 --> 00:40:27.900
Oh. <i>grazie. Papà.</i>

715
00:40:31.153 --> 00:40:33.406
Machiavelli! Don't you...

716
00:40:33.489 --> 00:40:35.908
No! Machiavelli!

717
00:40:38.327 --> 00:40:40.037
I'm so sorry about the cat.

718
00:40:40.121 --> 00:40:41.622
I don't know what got into him.

719
00:40:41.706 --> 00:40:44.583
It's fine. We're gonna head back to. uh...

720
00:40:45.126 --> 00:40:46.127
Oh!

721
00:40:46.210 --> 00:40:48.838
Do you guys need a place to stay?

722
00:40:50.619 --> 00:40:51.537
Cool.

723
00:40:51.704 --> 00:40:54.123
Oops! Sorry. This is my...

724
00:40:54.206 --> 00:40:55.207
Your hideout.

725
00:40:55.624 --> 00:40:57.960
Huh. Yeah. My hideout.

726
00:40:58.127 --> 00:41:00.045
<i>Buonanotte</i>. boys.

727
00:41:00.588 --> 00:41:01.589
Whoa!

728
00:41:02.882 --> 00:41:05.593
Slipped.
Uh. see you in the morning.

729
00:41:07.655 --> 00:41:09.157
- That was close.
- I know.

730
00:41:09.240 --> 00:41:11.075
Like. how big was that dad human?

731
00:41:11.159 --> 00:41:12.660
That guy kills things. for sure.

732
00:41:12.744 --> 00:41:14.579
I thought we were gonna die.
like. a hundred times.

733
00:41:14.662 --> 00:41:15.663
Hey. relax.

734
00:41:15.747 --> 00:41:17.498
We're incredible at this humaning stuff.

735
00:41:17.582 --> 00:41:19.459
Yeah. You're right.

736
00:41:19.542 --> 00:41:20.877
Did you see me on the bike?

737
00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:22.086
Giulia said. "Look up."

738
00:41:22.170 --> 00:41:23.504
and then all of a sudden. I was riding it.

739
00:41:23.588 --> 00:41:25.048
Yeah. yeah. yeah.
Our Vespa's gonna be

740
00:41:25.131 --> 00:41:26.883
even better than a bike. though.

741
00:41:26.966 --> 00:41:29.343
Because the moment we get it.
we're outta here.

742
00:41:31.345 --> 00:41:33.973
I can't wait.

743
00:41:50.364 --> 00:41:51.824
How could my mother tell him

744
00:41:51.908 --> 00:41:54.035
about this town of bloodthirsty lunatics?

745
00:41:54.118 --> 00:41:56.204
I still can't believe he would do this.

746
00:41:56.287 --> 00:41:57.288
It's not like him.

747
00:41:57.371 --> 00:41:58.539
Just keep your guard up.

748
00:41:58.623 --> 00:42:00.041
There's gonna be land monsters everywhere.

749
00:42:01.918 --> 00:42:04.879
- Daniela! Ooh! Wait! Ow! Ow!
- No! Not today. land monster!

750
00:42:04.962 --> 00:42:06.464
- It's me!
- Oh!

751
00:42:06.547 --> 00:42:08.049
You scared the scales off of me!

752
00:42:08.132 --> 00:42:09.425
Jeez. you're strong!

753
00:42:09.509 --> 00:42:10.802
I'm sorry. I'm just a little on edge.

754
00:42:10.885 --> 00:42:13.805
No. I needed that. It really woke me up.

755
00:42:13.971 --> 00:42:16.808
Wow! We look horrifying.

756
00:42:16.891 --> 00:42:18.351
Ugh. gross.

757
00:42:18.434 --> 00:42:20.228
Come on. Let's find our son.

758
00:42:36.494 --> 00:42:39.372
Oh. no! Oh. no!
Alberto! Wake up!

759
00:42:39.455 --> 00:42:41.290
What? Ahh! The sky's been leaking!

760
00:42:54.512 --> 00:42:56.389
Hmm. Uh...

761
00:42:56.472 --> 00:42:57.723
Oh. There you are!

762
00:42:58.015 --> 00:42:59.559
<i>Buongiorno.</i>

763
00:42:59.642 --> 00:43:00.768
All right. <i>ragazzi.</i>

764
00:43:00.852 --> 00:43:02.812
You want that entry fee.
you got to earn it.

765
00:43:02.895 --> 00:43:03.896
- Giulietta...
- I'm on it!

766
00:43:03.980 --> 00:43:06.357
- ...you make the deliveries.
- Already makin' 'em! <i>Ciao!</i>

767
00:43:06.440 --> 00:43:08.526
Hmm. You two are coming with me.

768
00:43:08.609 --> 00:43:09.610
Oh.

769
00:43:09.694 --> 00:43:11.487
Which knife do I get? Huh? Huh?

770
00:43:11.571 --> 00:43:12.864
You don't.

771
00:43:14.657 --> 00:43:16.033
<i>Buongiorno.</i> Massimo!

772
00:43:16.117 --> 00:43:18.703
You'll keep an eye out
for those sea monsters. right?

773
00:43:18.786 --> 00:43:20.163
We're all counting on you.

774
00:43:20.246 --> 00:43:23.291
Don't worry. Tommaso.
I've got my eyes peeled.

775
00:43:23.374 --> 00:43:24.792
They won't get away.

776
00:43:34.135 --> 00:43:36.179
Hey. this isn't a joyride.

777
00:43:36.262 --> 00:43:37.680
Make yourselves useful.

778
00:43:44.937 --> 00:43:45.938
Uh...

779
00:43:50.735 --> 00:43:52.987
Hey.
no goofing around back there.

780
00:44:15.176 --> 00:44:16.802
A sea monster ate it.

781
00:44:17.178 --> 00:44:18.304
Huh? What?

782
00:44:18.804 --> 00:44:22.808
<i>Ma. no.</i>
This is how I came into the world.

783
00:44:28.189 --> 00:44:29.190
Whoa.

784
00:44:29.273 --> 00:44:31.943
<i>Mannaggia.</i> not a great catch today.

785
00:44:32.026 --> 00:44:35.488
It might be because we're
over a haunted fish graveyard.

786
00:44:35.571 --> 00:44:38.449
We know it's not haunted.
The fish think it's haunted.

787
00:44:38.532 --> 00:44:42.203
This time of day. most fish
will be right about there.

788
00:44:43.496 --> 00:44:44.622
Hmm.

789
00:44:46.415 --> 00:44:47.875
- <i>Ciao.</i> Giulia.
- <i>Ciao.</i>

790
00:44:50.294 --> 00:44:51.462
Ha-ha!

791
00:44:51.545 --> 00:44:52.838
New personal best!

792
00:44:53.297 --> 00:44:55.299
<i>Santo pecorino.</i>

793
00:44:55.383 --> 00:44:56.592
Shoo! Shoo!

794
00:44:58.719 --> 00:45:01.180
Your friends do know fish.

795
00:45:01.430 --> 00:45:04.141
<i>Benissimo!</i>
Ooh. let's go sign up.

796
00:45:11.148 --> 00:45:12.191
Okay. Okay.

797
00:45:12.275 --> 00:45:14.110
Now. what's our plan? Think. Daniela.

798
00:45:14.193 --> 00:45:16.153
Hey. everything's always on you.

799
00:45:16.237 --> 00:45:17.488
I wanna step up.

800
00:45:17.571 --> 00:45:21.284
- Uh... You sure?
- Oh. yeah. I got this.

801
00:45:23.160 --> 00:45:25.496
Oh. hello there. young man.

802
00:45:25.579 --> 00:45:27.498
- You're not fooling anyone.
- Lorenzo. eh-eh.

803
00:45:27.581 --> 00:45:29.625
Did you really think
you could get away with this?

804
00:45:29.709 --> 00:45:31.836
- Renzo...
- You thought we wouldn't find you?

805
00:45:31.919 --> 00:45:33.170
- Well. guess what?
- I don't think...

806
00:45:33.254 --> 00:45:35.089
It's time for us to go home.

807
00:45:44.390 --> 00:45:46.684
Let that be a lesson to you!

808
00:45:46.767 --> 00:45:48.936
Go. go. go! Run before
its mother gets here!

809
00:45:49.895 --> 00:45:51.480
It turns out I don't got this.

810
00:45:51.564 --> 00:45:54.650
No. but I do. I'll know my son when I...

811
00:45:57.653 --> 00:45:58.863
...see him.

812
00:45:59.363 --> 00:46:00.573
Ah. sharks.

813
00:46:00.656 --> 00:46:03.409
<i>Grazie. Papà!</i>
Come on. we'd better hurry.

814
00:46:03.492 --> 00:46:05.411
Okay.

815
00:46:07.705 --> 00:46:08.748
Fellow Portorossans!

816
00:46:09.567 --> 00:46:12.070
It is I. Giorgio Giorgioni!

817
00:46:12.237 --> 00:46:16.866
Slayer of sea monsters
and beloved purveyor of pasta!

818
00:46:16.950 --> 00:46:18.493
Slayer of sea monsters?

819
00:46:18.576 --> 00:46:20.578
Ah. that's just <i>Signora</i> Marsigliese.

820
00:46:20.662 --> 00:46:22.455
She works for the sponsor for the race.

821
00:46:22.539 --> 00:46:24.415
This is gonna take forever.

822
00:46:24.499 --> 00:46:26.084
The finest pasta in Liguria

823
00:46:26.167 --> 00:46:28.211
at a price every family can afford.

824
00:46:28.294 --> 00:46:29.587
Get to the rules!

825
00:46:29.671 --> 00:46:32.549
Enthusiasm. Love to see it.

826
00:46:32.632 --> 00:46:34.342
To win my famous race.

827
00:46:34.425 --> 00:46:36.761
your team must be the first to brave

828
00:46:36.844 --> 00:46:38.555
the treacherous waters of the bay.

829
00:46:38.638 --> 00:46:41.266
devour a mystery bowl
of my delicious pasta.

830
00:46:41.349 --> 00:46:44.102
and ride to the top
of Mount Portorosso and back!

831
00:46:44.979 --> 00:46:46.564
That all sounds pretty hard.

832
00:46:46.647 --> 00:46:49.483
Yeah. Hard to lose. We're going to win.

833
00:46:49.567 --> 00:46:50.651
I love your confidence.

834
00:46:50.734 --> 00:46:52.403
But don't forget. we're going
to have to go through...

835
00:46:52.486 --> 00:46:53.863
Champion coming through.

836
00:46:53.946 --> 00:46:55.573
- Ugh.
<i>- Ciao. ciao!</i> Hey!

837
00:46:55.656 --> 00:46:56.657
Ercole.

838
00:46:57.157 --> 00:46:58.993
Aren't you a little old. Ercole?

839
00:46:59.076 --> 00:47:00.786
<i>Signora!</i> I am 16.

840
00:47:00.870 --> 00:47:02.288
You said that last year.

841
00:47:02.371 --> 00:47:03.747
But this year. it's true.

842
00:47:04.164 --> 00:47:06.292
You might want to
save your money. <i>ragazzi.</i>

843
00:47:06.375 --> 00:47:08.460
This year. Ercole's gonna
break the record

844
00:47:08.544 --> 00:47:10.337
and make it six in a row.

845
00:47:10.421 --> 00:47:12.882
Oh. no. I don't believe it.

846
00:47:12.965 --> 00:47:15.551
Spewlia. you teamed up
with these vagrants?

847
00:47:15.634 --> 00:47:16.802
Ignore him.

848
00:47:16.886 --> 00:47:18.178
Oh. I wish for you that you could.

849
00:47:18.262 --> 00:47:20.681
I'm afraid your friends still need to pay

850
00:47:20.764 --> 00:47:22.349
the out-of-town weirdo tax.

851
00:47:24.393 --> 00:47:26.395
Hey! Ercole!
You have to give it back!

852
00:47:26.907 --> 00:47:28.325
Ercole doesn't have to do anything.

853
00:47:28.409 --> 00:47:30.161
He's the Portorosso Cup champion.
number one.

854
00:47:30.244 --> 00:47:31.245
And number two.

855
00:47:31.328 --> 00:47:32.788
his life is amazing
and everyone loves him.

856
00:47:32.872 --> 00:47:35.291
They don't love you.
They're afraid of you.

857
00:47:35.374 --> 00:47:37.376
Raise your hand
if you love me.

858
00:47:37.626 --> 00:47:39.086
See? Everyone.

859
00:47:39.170 --> 00:47:40.754
Even you. Bop!

860
00:47:40.838 --> 00:47:42.423
Oh. that's it. Come on. Luca.

861
00:47:42.506 --> 00:47:44.383
Hey! The vagrants want to fight.

862
00:47:44.466 --> 00:47:45.301
Wow!

863
00:47:45.819 --> 00:47:47.237
- Alberto?
<i>- Silenzio. Bruno.</i>

864
00:47:47.321 --> 00:47:48.989
Remember. this is for our Vespa.

865
00:47:49.073 --> 00:47:50.365
- Stop.
- A Vespa?

866
00:47:51.533 --> 00:47:53.118
Trash like you can't ride Vespas.

867
00:47:53.202 --> 00:47:56.538
Ercole. you're just afraid
we're gonna put an end to your

868
00:47:56.622 --> 00:47:58.373
- evil empire of injustice.
- "Evil empire of injustice."

869
00:47:58.457 --> 00:47:59.917
Got anything new?

870
00:48:00.000 --> 00:48:03.337
Yeah. Here's a new one.
You look like a. uh... Uh...

871
00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:05.339
- A catfish.
- A catfish!

872
00:48:05.422 --> 00:48:06.799
Huh?

873
00:48:07.966 --> 00:48:08.967
Uh. they're bottom-feeders.

874
00:48:09.051 --> 00:48:10.719
and they also have
two sad little whiskers.

875
00:48:12.930 --> 00:48:14.056
Shut up!

876
00:48:16.577 --> 00:48:18.079
Listen. <i>piccoletto.</i>

877
00:48:18.329 --> 00:48:21.040
I eat kids like you for breakfast.

878
00:48:21.124 --> 00:48:24.043
I dunk them in my <i>cioccolata</i> and...

879
00:48:24.127 --> 00:48:25.670
...<i>finiti!</i>

880
00:48:27.547 --> 00:48:29.465
So. here. sign up. Mm?

881
00:48:29.549 --> 00:48:32.093
I'll make it my mission to destroy you.

882
00:48:32.176 --> 00:48:35.346
It's gonna be some race. huh?

883
00:48:35.805 --> 00:48:38.349
Sorry. no autographs today.

884
00:48:38.433 --> 00:48:40.017
You can put your hand down.

885
00:48:42.395 --> 00:48:44.314
Ha-ha! Luca! Bravo. we did it!

886
00:48:46.858 --> 00:48:47.901
Giulia Marcovaldo.

887
00:48:47.984 --> 00:48:49.819
<i>Ciao.</i> Giulia. Team of one?

888
00:48:49.903 --> 00:48:51.154
Not today.

889
00:48:51.321 --> 00:48:53.740
- Luca Paguro.
- Alberto Scorfano.

890
00:48:54.532 --> 00:48:57.035
{\an8}GIULIA: Okay. <i>ragazzi.</i>
we have one week to train.

891
00:48:59.412 --> 00:49:00.455
I got this.

892
00:49:00.789 --> 00:49:01.831
Wait. what?

893
00:49:01.915 --> 00:49:03.500
Every year they change the pasta.

894
00:49:03.583 --> 00:49:05.210
You have to be ready for anything.

895
00:49:05.293 --> 00:49:09.506
Could be cannelloni. penne.
fusilli. trofie. even lasagne.

896
00:49:10.423 --> 00:49:13.635
And you have to use a <i>forchetta.</i>
It's the rule.

897
00:49:13.718 --> 00:49:17.180
Ugh! Rules are for rule people.

898
00:49:28.358 --> 00:49:30.819
Holy carp. No. I can't.

899
00:49:30.902 --> 00:49:32.654
I know. I know.

900
00:49:33.363 --> 00:49:35.490
And remember. <i>piccoletto...</i>

901
00:49:37.492 --> 00:49:40.870
<i>Forza.</i> Luca. don't let him get
in your head. You can do this.

902
00:49:40.954 --> 00:49:44.249
Okay. <i>Silenzio. Bruno</i>. Here we go.

903
00:49:44.332 --> 00:49:46.584
I can't!

904
00:49:55.135 --> 00:49:57.220
I guess that's how humans swim?

905
00:49:57.303 --> 00:49:58.888
Ugh. that's embarrassing.

906
00:49:59.848 --> 00:50:00.974
Any sea monsters?

907
00:50:01.057 --> 00:50:04.477
No. But I see some bait.

908
00:50:07.021 --> 00:50:09.149
Oh. no! It's Ercole! Go. go!

909
00:50:09.816 --> 00:50:11.651
- Luca! Faster. faster!
- Why aren't we moving?

910
00:50:12.235 --> 00:50:13.611
Ercole?

911
00:50:18.408 --> 00:50:19.576
- Guido!
- I... I slipped.

912
00:50:19.659 --> 00:50:20.910
Ciccio. slap Guido.

913
00:50:21.161 --> 00:50:22.412
Again. Like you mean it.

914
00:50:25.874 --> 00:50:27.167
Huh?

915
00:50:28.168 --> 00:50:29.836
Hmm. Where did the other one go?

916
00:50:32.046 --> 00:50:33.715
- Eh?
- Ercole!

917
00:50:33.798 --> 00:50:35.884
Whoa!

918
00:50:37.051 --> 00:50:40.054
Giulia! It is wool. It cannot get wet!

919
00:50:40.138 --> 00:50:42.140
Ciccio. make it dry. <i>subito!</i>

920
00:50:42.223 --> 00:50:44.392
Luca? Alberto?

921
00:50:44.768 --> 00:50:45.852
Are you okay?

922
00:50:45.935 --> 00:50:47.353
- Um...
- We're good! Good. good. good.

923
00:50:47.437 --> 00:50:49.481
Well. I think that's
enough training for today.

924
00:50:49.564 --> 00:50:50.982
- Yeah. Agreed.
- Yup.

925
00:50:51.691 --> 00:50:55.320
Ah. Ciccio! The motor!
They are slowly getting away!

926
00:50:56.488 --> 00:50:57.697
Guido. slap Ciccio.

927
00:50:58.865 --> 00:51:00.200
With contempt!

928
00:51:02.035 --> 00:51:03.495
- Huh?
- Hmm.

929
00:51:08.249 --> 00:51:09.626
Hey!

930
00:51:09.709 --> 00:51:10.710
Kick it.

931
00:51:13.505 --> 00:51:14.506
Oh!

932
00:51:15.965 --> 00:51:17.258
I have an idea.

933
00:51:17.342 --> 00:51:18.343
Uh-uh. Honey?

934
00:51:18.426 --> 00:51:20.261
Hey. guys! Can I play. too?

935
00:51:20.345 --> 00:51:21.346
Oops. sorry!

936
00:51:21.429 --> 00:51:22.472
I'm not used to legs.

937
00:51:22.555 --> 00:51:23.973
Oh. Okay.

938
00:51:25.141 --> 00:51:26.226
Get the ball!

939
00:51:26.309 --> 00:51:27.310
Come and get it!

940
00:51:28.228 --> 00:51:29.521
Uh-uh!

941
00:51:30.396 --> 00:51:31.981
Not our kid. not our kid.

942
00:51:42.951 --> 00:51:44.410
Ha-ha!

943
00:51:48.206 --> 00:51:51.084
Let's see Bianca Branzino do that!

944
00:51:52.335 --> 00:51:53.336
Good effort. team.

945
00:51:53.419 --> 00:51:54.420
You've earned your pasta tonight.

946
00:51:54.504 --> 00:51:55.505
Can I please eat with my hands?

947
00:51:55.588 --> 00:51:56.589
Where could he be?

948
00:51:56.673 --> 00:51:58.675
Well. at least you won. I think.

949
00:51:58.758 --> 00:52:00.385
Yeah. I guess I did.

950
00:52:00.468 --> 00:52:02.262
Come on. We just gotta keep looking.

951
00:52:07.892 --> 00:52:08.977
Uh...

952
00:52:09.060 --> 00:52:12.063
Alberto? I think
I might've seen my parents.

953
00:52:12.146 --> 00:52:14.399
No way. I told you.
they're not coming here.

954
00:52:14.482 --> 00:52:15.817
But what if they did?

955
00:52:15.900 --> 00:52:17.110
They're gonna send me to the deep.

956
00:52:17.193 --> 00:52:19.070
Listen. relax. It's never gonna happen.

957
00:52:19.153 --> 00:52:20.154
All right. boys.

958
00:52:20.238 --> 00:52:22.407
Pretty good today.
but let's talk technique.

959
00:52:22.490 --> 00:52:25.201
Hey. <i>ragazzi!</i> I need some help
with the nets.

960
00:52:25.285 --> 00:52:27.662
You. The big. strong one.

961
00:52:27.745 --> 00:52:29.038
<i>- Andiamo.</i>
- I'll be right back.

962
00:52:34.377 --> 00:52:35.837
Hey. we're gonna win.

963
00:52:36.004 --> 00:52:37.881
And you'll get your Vespa.

964
00:52:38.298 --> 00:52:40.008
Why do you want a Vespa. again?

965
00:52:40.091 --> 00:52:41.926
Oh. Because it'll be amazing.

966
00:52:42.010 --> 00:52:44.888
Every day. me and Alberto
are gonna ride someplace new.

967
00:52:44.971 --> 00:52:47.515
And every night.
we'll sleep under the fish.

968
00:52:47.599 --> 00:52:50.560
The fish? Good.

969
00:52:50.643 --> 00:52:52.979
How about you?
What'll you do when you win?

970
00:52:53.062 --> 00:52:55.273
I'll get up
in front of everyone

971
00:52:55.356 --> 00:52:57.358
and say. "Told you I'd win!"

972
00:52:57.442 --> 00:52:58.693
Yeah.

973
00:52:59.068 --> 00:53:00.278
And then what?

974
00:53:00.445 --> 00:53:01.863
Well. that's it.

975
00:53:01.946 --> 00:53:03.156
Look. during school.

976
00:53:03.239 --> 00:53:05.116
I live with my <i>mamma</i> in Genova.

977
00:53:05.199 --> 00:53:06.993
And every summer. I come here.

978
00:53:07.076 --> 00:53:09.662
and everyone thinks
I'm just some weird kid

979
00:53:09.746 --> 00:53:11.289
who doesn't belong.

980
00:53:12.874 --> 00:53:14.208
I think I know how you feel.

981
00:53:14.292 --> 00:53:16.210
Right? That's why we gotta win.

982
00:53:16.294 --> 00:53:17.629
The town will cheer our names.

983
00:53:18.046 --> 00:53:20.757
Ercole's life will be ruined!

984
00:53:20.840 --> 00:53:22.091
Sorry. Too much?

985
00:53:22.175 --> 00:53:24.177
My mom says sometimes I'm too much.

986
00:53:24.260 --> 00:53:26.054
No way. Not for me.

987
00:53:27.639 --> 00:53:30.183
You know those aren't fish. right?

988
00:53:30.266 --> 00:53:33.436
Of course they are.
Alberto told me all about it.

989
00:53:33.937 --> 00:53:34.938
Come with me.

990
00:53:57.473 --> 00:53:58.849
This is a telescope.

991
00:53:59.016 --> 00:54:01.018
Old man Bernardi lets me use it.

992
00:54:01.101 --> 00:54:04.271
It makes faraway things seem close. Look.

993
00:54:08.150 --> 00:54:09.735
See any fish?

994
00:54:09.818 --> 00:54:11.278
Then what are all those?

995
00:54:11.361 --> 00:54:13.071
Stars. Like the sun.

996
00:54:13.155 --> 00:54:15.324
Giant. raging balls of fire!

997
00:54:15.491 --> 00:54:17.409
So. Alberto was wrong.

998
00:54:17.493 --> 00:54:19.495
And stars are circled by planets.

999
00:54:23.040 --> 00:54:24.041
Look.

1000
00:54:25.042 --> 00:54:26.919
That's <i>Saturno</i>. It's my favorite.

1001
00:54:27.002 --> 00:54:28.837
It's the lightest of the planets.

1002
00:54:28.921 --> 00:54:31.840
They say if there was an ocean
big enough to hold it.

1003
00:54:31.924 --> 00:54:32.966
it would float in it!

1004
00:54:33.050 --> 00:54:33.675
Whoa!

1005
00:54:36.696 --> 00:54:37.697
Wow!

1006
00:54:43.077 --> 00:54:44.454
Come on. Luca!

1007
00:55:11.879 --> 00:55:12.963
{\an8}LUCA: So. this is how machines fly?

1008
00:55:13.047 --> 00:55:14.048
{\an8}GIULIA: <i>Sì.</i>

1009
00:55:14.131 --> 00:55:15.674
{\an8}LUCA: And there are big towns
called cities?

1010
00:55:15.758 --> 00:55:16.759
{\an8}GIULIA: <i>Sì.</i>

1011
00:55:16.842 --> 00:55:18.052
Like even bigger than Portorosso?

1012
00:55:18.135 --> 00:55:20.304
Like Genova! Literally 20 times bigger.

1013
00:55:20.387 --> 00:55:22.348
And we're all on a big round rock.

1014
00:55:22.431 --> 00:55:23.724
floating around a star

1015
00:55:23.807 --> 00:55:25.768
in the "solar system"?

1016
00:55:25.851 --> 00:55:27.227
So cool. right?

1017
00:55:27.311 --> 00:55:29.438
And is there anything
beyond the solar system?

1018
00:55:29.521 --> 00:55:31.982
Only a galaxy full of solar systems.

1019
00:55:32.066 --> 00:55:34.610
- Then what?
- A universe full of galaxies!

1020
00:55:34.693 --> 00:55:36.487
And then what?

1021
00:55:36.570 --> 00:55:37.905
And then...

1022
00:55:38.238 --> 00:55:39.281
I don't know.

1023
00:55:39.365 --> 00:55:41.325
But next year in Advanced Astronomy.

1024
00:55:41.408 --> 00:55:43.035
I'm gonna use my school's telescope.

1025
00:55:43.118 --> 00:55:44.286
So. maybe I'll find out.

1026
00:55:44.578 --> 00:55:47.498
That thing's huge.
I wish I could show it to you.

1027
00:55:47.581 --> 00:55:50.167
Just promise you'll tell me
everything you see!

1028
00:55:50.542 --> 00:55:52.044
Sorry. Too much?

1029
00:55:52.127 --> 00:55:53.462
Never.

1030
00:55:54.630 --> 00:55:56.548
Hey. Luca. I've been looking
everywhere for you.

1031
00:55:56.632 --> 00:55:58.842
- Oh. sorry.
- Just come on. Let's go.

1032
00:55:59.009 --> 00:56:02.096
Could I maybe borrow this?
Just for tonight.

1033
00:56:04.621 --> 00:56:05.914
You can have it.

1034
00:56:07.931 --> 00:56:08.807
Ha-ha!

1035
00:56:09.474 --> 00:56:12.269
The universe is literally yours!

1036
00:56:12.352 --> 00:56:13.812
Wow. Thank you!

1037
00:56:13.896 --> 00:56:14.938
Luca!

1038
00:56:15.022 --> 00:56:16.231
Okay.

1039
00:56:21.195 --> 00:56:22.196
Where are we going?

1040
00:56:22.279 --> 00:56:23.822
Come on.
I got something to show you.

1041
00:56:24.281 --> 00:56:27.576
Hey. you won't believe this.
Those aren't fish.

1042
00:56:27.659 --> 00:56:28.702
- What?
- Yeah.

1043
00:56:28.785 --> 00:56:30.162
Giulia explained it to me.

1044
00:56:30.245 --> 00:56:31.246
They're fires.

1045
00:56:31.330 --> 00:56:33.624
But. like. one million times bigger.

1046
00:56:33.707 --> 00:56:35.417
Uh. no. they're not.

1047
00:56:38.545 --> 00:56:41.506
Soon you'll be ours. sweet Vespa.

1048
00:56:41.673 --> 00:56:42.674
Take a look.

1049
00:56:42.758 --> 00:56:44.718
I thought of every
single thing we're gonna need.

1050
00:56:44.801 --> 00:56:46.053
{\an8}Also. I added flames.

1051
00:56:46.553 --> 00:56:48.013
That's so cool!

1052
00:56:48.430 --> 00:56:51.016
Oh! And we can bring
a telescope. too!

1053
00:56:51.099 --> 00:56:53.185
Yeah! That shoots lightning!

1054
00:56:53.268 --> 00:56:54.269
No. no. no.

1055
00:56:54.436 --> 00:56:55.938
You look through it.

1056
00:56:56.271 --> 00:56:59.358
Giulia says there's an even
bigger one at her school.

1057
00:56:59.566 --> 00:57:01.443
Wait. What if we visit her there?

1058
00:57:01.526 --> 00:57:03.153
Why would you wanna do that?

1059
00:57:03.675 --> 00:57:05.135
It kinda sounds interesting.

1060
00:57:05.218 --> 00:57:07.846
The whole reason we're getting a Vespa
is to live on our own.

1061
00:57:07.930 --> 00:57:10.515
We don't need school.
We don't need anybody.

1062
00:57:10.599 --> 00:57:12.559
Couldn't we just try it?

1063
00:57:12.643 --> 00:57:14.186
Just for a few days?

1064
00:57:14.269 --> 00:57:16.855
Luca. sea monsters can't go to school.

1065
00:57:16.939 --> 00:57:18.231
What do you think is gonna happen

1066
00:57:18.747 --> 00:57:19.915
when they see your fish face?

1067
00:57:23.210 --> 00:57:25.087
Hey. look who it is.

1068
00:57:25.170 --> 00:57:27.339
And with no Giulia to hide behind.

1069
00:57:27.423 --> 00:57:29.049
- Come on. Let's go.
- No.

1070
00:57:29.133 --> 00:57:31.051
Something's fishy with you two.

1071
00:57:31.135 --> 00:57:32.720
I mean. besides the smell.

1072
00:57:32.803 --> 00:57:34.013
You're hiding something.

1073
00:57:34.263 --> 00:57:36.181
Is it that we're smarter than you?

1074
00:57:36.265 --> 00:57:38.267
I mean. we're not really hiding that.

1075
00:57:38.350 --> 00:57:39.727
It's just kind of obvious.

1076
00:57:39.810 --> 00:57:41.937
You know. people think I'm a nice guy.

1077
00:57:42.021 --> 00:57:43.522
Always joking around.

1078
00:57:43.605 --> 00:57:45.858
But really. I'm not.

1079
00:57:45.941 --> 00:57:47.985
- Stop!
- Wait your turn. <i>piccoletto.</i>

1080
00:57:48.068 --> 00:57:50.487
I want to make myself very clear.

1081
00:57:50.571 --> 00:57:52.072
This is my town.

1082
00:57:52.156 --> 00:57:53.282
number one...

1083
00:57:53.365 --> 00:57:56.994
...and number two. I don't want you in it.

1084
00:57:57.411 --> 00:57:58.871
I... I said stop!

1085
00:57:59.246 --> 00:58:02.332
Put that down. <i>piccoletto.</i>
You'll hurt yourself.

1086
00:58:02.416 --> 00:58:03.667
Let him go!

1087
00:58:05.849 --> 00:58:09.269
Go. Now. Before I change my mind.

1088
00:58:09.853 --> 00:58:13.565
Nobody wants you here. <i>idioti!</i>
Keep running!

1089
00:58:16.484 --> 00:58:19.070
Why did you make him mad?
We should've left.

1090
00:58:19.154 --> 00:58:20.572
No. no. no. We're fine.

1091
00:58:20.947 --> 00:58:22.449
I had it under control.

1092
00:58:22.616 --> 00:58:25.702
All you gotta do
is follow my lead. remember?

1093
00:58:35.767 --> 00:58:37.268
Rise and shine!

1094
00:58:39.145 --> 00:58:41.606
Go. go! Go. Alberto! Go!

1095
00:58:55.568 --> 00:58:57.278
Nope. Whoa...

1096
00:59:02.397 --> 00:59:03.690
<i>Buongiorno!</i>

1097
00:59:10.113 --> 00:59:11.782
Sea monster!

1098
00:59:13.867 --> 00:59:14.952
Whew.

1099
00:59:16.245 --> 00:59:17.704
Oh.

1100
00:59:19.957 --> 00:59:20.958
Wha...

1101
00:59:21.041 --> 00:59:22.125
Ugo?

1102
00:59:28.173 --> 00:59:29.550
Rise and shine!

1103
00:59:29.633 --> 00:59:31.510
Only two days till the race.

1104
00:59:31.802 --> 00:59:32.803
Hmm.

1105
00:59:34.388 --> 00:59:35.597
Espresso.

1106
00:59:40.759 --> 00:59:41.885
Go. Luca!

1107
00:59:41.968 --> 00:59:42.969
Go. go!

1108
00:59:43.219 --> 00:59:44.721
Hey. don't cheer for him!

1109
00:59:45.889 --> 00:59:47.807
Ha-ha! Whoo!

1110
00:59:48.850 --> 00:59:50.852
This is fun!

1111
00:59:50.935 --> 00:59:52.687
Uh...

1112
00:59:53.313 --> 00:59:54.356
Hmm.

1113
00:59:57.734 --> 00:59:58.735
Mm?

1114
01:00:01.905 --> 01:00:03.156
Huh. Hey!

1115
01:00:03.239 --> 01:00:04.949
{\an8} That's amazing!

1116
01:00:05.033 --> 01:00:06.076
{\an8}

1117
01:00:06.159 --> 01:00:07.369
{\an8}- LUCA: Oh. wow!

1118
01:00:13.875 --> 01:00:17.170
I don't know. Lorenzo.
Was I too hard on him?

1119
01:00:17.253 --> 01:00:20.590
No. You were just trying
to keep him safe.

1120
01:00:20.882 --> 01:00:21.966
It's my fault.

1121
01:00:22.050 --> 01:00:25.095
I wasn't paying enough attention to him.

1122
01:00:25.178 --> 01:00:28.390
But I was the one who tried
to send him away.

1123
01:00:28.473 --> 01:00:30.558
I just never in a million years

1124
01:00:30.642 --> 01:00:31.976
would have thought he'd do this.

1125
01:00:32.060 --> 01:00:33.061
It's like I don't even know...

1126
01:00:33.144 --> 01:00:34.145
You can do it. Luca!

1127
01:00:35.063 --> 01:00:36.356
...who he is!

1128
01:00:36.439 --> 01:00:37.732
Go. go!

1129
01:00:37.816 --> 01:00:39.067
- Luca!
- Luca!

1130
01:00:39.609 --> 01:00:40.610
Luca. stop!

1131
01:00:41.945 --> 01:00:42.946
Luca!

1132
01:00:45.782 --> 01:00:46.950
Where are we going?

1133
01:00:47.033 --> 01:00:48.576
Uh... A shortcut.

1134
01:00:48.660 --> 01:00:51.079
Steeper. rough terrain... I like it.

1135
01:00:51.246 --> 01:00:52.872
Why aren't you training?

1136
01:00:53.039 --> 01:00:54.874
I'm always training.

1137
01:01:00.922 --> 01:01:04.008
Bravo. Luca. That was your fastest yet.

1138
01:01:04.092 --> 01:01:05.552
Ooh. guys. look!

1139
01:01:05.885 --> 01:01:07.345
That's the train to Genova.

1140
01:01:07.429 --> 01:01:08.721
That goes to your school?

1141
01:01:08.805 --> 01:01:09.806
Yeah.

1142
01:01:09.889 --> 01:01:11.516
I was wondering. actually.

1143
01:01:11.599 --> 01:01:14.227
is your school open to everyone?

1144
01:01:14.310 --> 01:01:17.147
Well. it costs a little money.
but I guess.

1145
01:01:17.230 --> 01:01:18.565
Great. Thank you. Giulia.

1146
01:01:18.648 --> 01:01:20.275
for showing us the boring thing

1147
01:01:20.358 --> 01:01:21.901
that takes us to the terrible place.

1148
01:01:21.985 --> 01:01:23.862
Now. can we focus on what matters?

1149
01:01:23.945 --> 01:01:26.739
If we lose this race.
we're not going anywhere.

1150
01:01:26.948 --> 01:01:29.492
<i>Santa mozzarella</i>. The downhill.

1151
01:01:29.576 --> 01:01:30.577
I know it looks scary.

1152
01:01:30.660 --> 01:01:31.661
But here's what you need to know...

1153
01:01:31.744 --> 01:01:32.871
Would you stop bossing him around?

1154
01:01:32.954 --> 01:01:33.955
What is your problem?

1155
01:01:34.038 --> 01:01:36.166
I'm his friend. I know what he needs.

1156
01:01:36.249 --> 01:01:37.834
Oh. yeah?
Well. then. what does he need?

1157
01:01:37.917 --> 01:01:40.628
Me. We'll just ride it
like we did on the island. Together.

1158
01:01:41.379 --> 01:01:42.547
<i>- Andiamo.</i>
- No!

1159
01:01:43.006 --> 01:01:44.215
Alberto. stop!

1160
01:01:44.299 --> 01:01:45.633
That's Bruno talking!

1161
01:01:45.717 --> 01:01:48.303
No! I'm pretty sure that's just me!

1162
01:01:53.641 --> 01:01:54.976
- Stop. Alberto!
- Let it go!

1163
01:01:55.059 --> 01:01:56.060
Look out!

1164
01:02:02.817 --> 01:02:05.320
<i>Porca paletta.</i> what was that?

1165
01:02:05.403 --> 01:02:06.404
Huh?

1166
01:02:06.488 --> 01:02:09.073
Bah! Not now. Ciccio! Eyes on the water!

1167
01:02:09.157 --> 01:02:10.408
- Move. move!
- Okay.

1168
01:02:13.828 --> 01:02:16.581
Oh. no!
Luca! Alberto!

1169
01:02:17.081 --> 01:02:18.750
She'll see us. Come on!

1170
01:02:23.463 --> 01:02:25.757
Look. I was just trying to
show you how to do it right.

1171
01:02:25.840 --> 01:02:27.383
You don't know how to do it right!

1172
01:02:27.467 --> 01:02:28.801
I got us down the hill. didn't I?

1173
01:02:28.885 --> 01:02:30.970
You crashed! Into the sea!

1174
01:02:31.054 --> 01:02:32.138
It's fine.

1175
01:02:32.222 --> 01:02:34.891
Nothing's fine! My parents just saw me!

1176
01:02:34.974 --> 01:02:36.392
Luca. your parents aren't here.

1177
01:02:36.476 --> 01:02:38.061
You don't know what you're talking about!

1178
01:02:38.144 --> 01:02:39.979
Look. this town is making you crazy.

1179
01:02:40.063 --> 01:02:42.607
We just need to win that Vespa
and get outta here.

1180
01:02:43.066 --> 01:02:45.026
It's not gonna be any different.

1181
01:02:45.360 --> 01:02:46.694
I don't wanna...

1182
01:02:49.822 --> 01:02:51.324
I wanna go to school.

1183
01:02:51.491 --> 01:02:53.868
That again? We can't go to school.

1184
01:02:53.952 --> 01:02:55.328
You're just afraid you can't do it.

1185
01:02:55.411 --> 01:02:56.871
I'm not afraid.

1186
01:02:56.955 --> 01:02:58.206
You're the one who gets afraid.

1187
01:02:58.289 --> 01:02:59.582
Shut up!

1188
01:03:02.085 --> 01:03:03.086
Ow!

1189
01:03:04.420 --> 01:03:05.880
What happens when she sees you?

1190
01:03:05.964 --> 01:03:06.965
When anyone sees you?

1191
01:03:07.048 --> 01:03:08.383
Get off me!

1192
01:03:08.466 --> 01:03:10.385
You're alive!

1193
01:03:14.347 --> 01:03:16.724
Hey! You're never allowed
on my bike again.

1194
01:03:16.808 --> 01:03:18.476
Stick to food. big guy.

1195
01:03:21.187 --> 01:03:23.314
Uh. what's going on?

1196
01:03:23.398 --> 01:03:24.691
Nothing. Let's just get back to training.

1197
01:03:24.774 --> 01:03:27.026
Actually. we have something to ask you.

1198
01:03:27.110 --> 01:03:28.236
We were wondering

1199
01:03:28.319 --> 01:03:30.280
if we could come with you to your school?

1200
01:03:31.114 --> 01:03:34.409
<i>Santo pecorino!</i> That's the best idea ever!

1201
01:03:34.492 --> 01:03:36.744
Yes! Of course!

1202
01:03:41.124 --> 01:03:43.042
Uh. Giulia. your school.

1203
01:03:43.126 --> 01:03:45.086
does it take all kinds of people?

1204
01:03:45.545 --> 01:03:47.880
I mean. what if some of them
were not human?

1205
01:03:47.964 --> 01:03:49.048
Alberto...

1206
01:03:49.132 --> 01:03:52.719
What if some were. oh.
I don't know. sea monsters?

1207
01:03:52.802 --> 01:03:53.803
Sea monsters?

1208
01:03:53.886 --> 01:03:56.889
I doubt your school would even
accept sea monsters. right?

1209
01:03:58.099 --> 01:03:59.851
Ah. that's a weird joke. Alberto.

1210
01:03:59.934 --> 01:04:01.769
Yeah. I know. it's kinda hard to imagine.

1211
01:04:01.853 --> 01:04:03.021
So. let me just show you!

1212
01:04:03.104 --> 01:04:04.272
No!

1213
01:04:05.440 --> 01:04:07.066
- Come on.
- Giulia. wait!

1214
01:04:07.150 --> 01:04:08.901
We don't have time to goof around.

1215
01:04:08.985 --> 01:04:10.695
Huh?

1216
01:04:16.200 --> 01:04:17.201
Help!

1217
01:04:17.660 --> 01:04:18.828
Don't hurt us!

1218
01:04:18.911 --> 01:04:20.538
- See? I knew this would...
- Sea monster!

1219
01:04:21.831 --> 01:04:23.458
Did you hear that? This way.

1220
01:04:23.541 --> 01:04:25.293
Luca?

1221
01:04:27.712 --> 01:04:28.880
Stay back!

1222
01:04:29.839 --> 01:04:32.216
Sea monster! There it is!

1223
01:04:36.512 --> 01:04:38.139
<i>Ragazzi.</i> now!

1224
01:04:38.222 --> 01:04:39.223
No!

1225
01:04:44.604 --> 01:04:46.773
Ah. <i>idioti.</i> you let it get away!

1226
01:04:46.856 --> 01:04:47.857
To the boat!

1227
01:04:47.940 --> 01:04:49.484
We're gonna kill a sea monster!

1228
01:05:03.671 --> 01:05:06.841
Oh. there you are. I made your favorite.

1229
01:05:06.925 --> 01:05:08.384
trenette al pesto.

1230
01:05:09.094 --> 01:05:10.220
Where's Alberto?

1231
01:05:10.747 --> 01:05:13.500
Uh. he left. <i>Signor</i> Marcovaldo.

1232
01:05:17.879 --> 01:05:19.423
Do you know where he went?

1233
01:05:19.506 --> 01:05:21.466
No. But I don't think

1234
01:05:21.550 --> 01:05:23.010
he wants anyone looking for him.

1235
01:05:23.385 --> 01:05:25.721
Maybe not. But just in case.

1236
01:05:29.516 --> 01:05:30.559
Okay.

1237
01:05:30.642 --> 01:05:31.852
Well. the two of us can still do the race.

1238
01:05:32.477 --> 01:05:34.896
You'll swim. you'll eat.
you've done both before...

1239
01:05:34.980 --> 01:05:36.398
- Luca. I...
- ...and I'll do the ride.

1240
01:05:36.481 --> 01:05:37.899
I mean. that's allowed. right?

1241
01:05:37.983 --> 01:05:39.568
- Luca. Luca?
- It should be fine.

1242
01:05:39.651 --> 01:05:40.944
- we're still okay...
- Luca!

1243
01:05:44.698 --> 01:05:47.159
Sleeping under the fish.
Now I get it.

1244
01:05:47.242 --> 01:05:48.285
Uh. I can explain.

1245
01:05:48.368 --> 01:05:51.079
Of all the places
for sea monsters to visit.

1246
01:05:51.163 --> 01:05:52.456
Portorosso?

1247
01:05:52.539 --> 01:05:54.166
Have you seen this town?

1248
01:05:54.249 --> 01:05:56.668
My father hunts sea monsters!

1249
01:05:57.044 --> 01:05:58.837
Luca. you have to get out of here.

1250
01:05:58.920 --> 01:06:00.922
But I thought we were underdogs.

1251
01:06:01.435 --> 01:06:03.979
Do you think I want you to leave?

1252
01:06:04.063 --> 01:06:06.691
This is the happiest I've...

1253
01:06:06.774 --> 01:06:08.651
Look. it's just not worth it.

1254
01:06:08.734 --> 01:06:10.444
You don't understand.

1255
01:06:10.528 --> 01:06:12.238
No. I don't.

1256
01:06:12.321 --> 01:06:14.949
Risking your life for a Vespa?

1257
01:06:15.282 --> 01:06:17.159
My parents were gonna send me away.

1258
01:06:18.577 --> 01:06:20.996
That's why we did all of this.

1259
01:06:23.874 --> 01:06:25.876
But it's over now.

1260
01:06:30.047 --> 01:06:31.632
Goodbye. Giulia.

1261
01:06:32.133 --> 01:06:33.467
I'm sorry.

1262
01:07:15.553 --> 01:07:16.846
Alberto?

1263
01:07:25.521 --> 01:07:27.148
What are you doing here?

1264
01:07:27.857 --> 01:07:28.900
I'm...

1265
01:07:29.859 --> 01:07:30.860
I'm sorry.

1266
01:07:32.195 --> 01:07:34.572
I... I never should've done that.

1267
01:07:34.656 --> 01:07:35.782
I wish I could take it back.

1268
01:07:35.865 --> 01:07:38.951
Yeah. whatever. You're sorry.
Now. just go away!

1269
01:07:57.637 --> 01:07:58.638
Alberto?

1270
01:07:59.263 --> 01:08:01.307
What are those marks on the wall?

1271
01:08:02.975 --> 01:08:04.686
Tell me what they mean.

1272
01:08:07.814 --> 01:08:09.607
I started when my dad left.

1273
01:08:11.067 --> 01:08:14.904
You were living here alone
for that many days?

1274
01:08:16.781 --> 01:08:19.075
I just stopped counting after a while.

1275
01:08:19.909 --> 01:08:21.953
He said I was old enough to be on my own.

1276
01:08:24.789 --> 01:08:26.416
I just thought that...

1277
01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:29.419
...maybe he'd change his mind.

1278
01:08:31.212 --> 01:08:32.714
Honestly. though. I get it.

1279
01:08:33.089 --> 01:08:34.549
He's better off without me.

1280
01:08:35.383 --> 01:08:36.384
You are. too.

1281
01:08:36.467 --> 01:08:37.593
That's not true.

1282
01:08:37.677 --> 01:08:38.761
Yes. it is.

1283
01:08:38.845 --> 01:08:41.097
You're not like me. You're the good kid.

1284
01:08:41.597 --> 01:08:44.058
And I'm just
the kid that ruins everything.

1285
01:08:44.434 --> 01:08:48.187
<i>Silenzio. Bruno</i>. That's just
the dumb voice in your head.

1286
01:08:48.271 --> 01:08:49.439
You taught me that.

1287
01:08:49.522 --> 01:08:51.691
And getting a Vespa? Seeing the world...

1288
01:08:51.774 --> 01:08:53.359
Just let it go! Okay?

1289
01:08:53.443 --> 01:08:55.236
Look. you and I
should've never been friends

1290
01:08:55.319 --> 01:08:56.320
in the first place.

1291
01:08:57.113 --> 01:08:58.448
Don't say that.

1292
01:08:58.531 --> 01:09:00.116
- Alberto?
- Get outta here!

1293
01:09:00.199 --> 01:09:02.118
I'm not gonna tell you again.

1294
01:09:07.457 --> 01:09:09.292
Okay. I'll go.

1295
01:09:10.042 --> 01:09:11.210
I'll go win the race.

1296
01:09:11.878 --> 01:09:13.296
- What?
- Yeah.

1297
01:09:13.755 --> 01:09:16.716
Yeah! And then the Vespa will be ours!

1298
01:09:16.799 --> 01:09:18.593
And we'll ride away together!

1299
01:09:18.676 --> 01:09:20.470
Luca. that's crazy.

1300
01:09:20.553 --> 01:09:21.721
Well. maybe I'm crazy.

1301
01:09:21.804 --> 01:09:23.431
Take me. gravity!

1302
01:09:23.514 --> 01:09:24.599
Luca!

1303
01:09:24.682 --> 01:09:26.684
Ow.

1304
01:09:27.018 --> 01:09:28.144
What are you doing?

1305
01:09:28.667 --> 01:09:30.836
I'm okay. I'll be back tomorrow.

1306
01:09:30.920 --> 01:09:32.838
I'm gonna fix this!

1307
01:09:38.427 --> 01:09:40.471
You want to split up your team?

1308
01:09:40.554 --> 01:09:42.139
Yes. If it's allowed.

1309
01:09:42.222 --> 01:09:44.016
Luca? What are you doing here?

1310
01:09:44.099 --> 01:09:45.893
Don't worry. I'll race on my own.

1311
01:09:46.875 --> 01:09:48.377
You can if you want.
but I don't recommend it.

1312
01:09:48.460 --> 01:09:49.545
Thank you!

1313
01:09:49.628 --> 01:09:51.004
But how are you gonna...

1314
01:09:51.088 --> 01:09:53.423
I mean. what happens when the...

1315
01:09:53.507 --> 01:09:55.134
You can't swim!

1316
01:09:55.217 --> 01:09:56.635
Alone again?

1317
01:09:59.346 --> 01:10:00.347
Hmm.

1318
01:10:00.430 --> 01:10:01.431
- Ah. volunteers...
- Huh?

1319
01:10:01.515 --> 01:10:02.516
- ...you're late.
- Huh?

1320
01:10:02.599 --> 01:10:03.600
One cup for each kid.

1321
01:10:03.684 --> 01:10:04.685
Oh!

1322
01:10:04.768 --> 01:10:06.019
- Yeah. One cup per kid.
- Yes.

1323
01:10:06.103 --> 01:10:07.104
- Got it.
- Here.

1324
01:10:07.187 --> 01:10:09.606
For when Giulia. you know. she...

1325
01:10:20.910 --> 01:10:23.621
Ciccio. hold still. <i>Olio d'oliva.</i>

1326
01:10:23.704 --> 01:10:25.748
He will cut through the water
like a knife.

1327
01:10:25.831 --> 01:10:27.917
- Oh! Ah.
- An oily knife.

1328
01:10:28.626 --> 01:10:29.627
Huh?

1329
01:10:29.710 --> 01:10:31.253
Huh?

1330
01:10:37.051 --> 01:10:38.969
This makes me laugh.

1331
01:10:40.221 --> 01:10:42.306
I guess even your terrible friends

1332
01:10:42.390 --> 01:10:43.474
don't want to be friends.

1333
01:10:43.557 --> 01:10:46.394
Luca! This is a very bad idea!

1334
01:10:46.477 --> 01:10:47.812
Hey. vagrant!

1335
01:10:48.315 --> 01:10:50.401
Can't afford a proper swimsuit?

1336
01:10:50.484 --> 01:10:51.860
<i>Signore e signori.</i>

1337
01:10:51.944 --> 01:10:54.905
the Portorosso Cup is about to begin!

1338
01:10:54.989 --> 01:10:57.449
We know there's been
a few sightings lately.

1339
01:10:57.533 --> 01:10:58.867
but fear not!

1340
01:10:58.951 --> 01:11:00.911
If any sea monsters show up today.

1341
01:11:00.995 --> 01:11:02.496
we are ready for them.

1342
01:11:05.097 --> 01:11:07.433
Swimmers. take your mark!

1343
01:11:46.819 --> 01:11:48.487
Ow! Ow! Ow!

1344
01:11:50.823 --> 01:11:51.824
What?

1345
01:11:59.498 --> 01:12:01.000
Swim. Ciccio! Come on!

1346
01:12:01.083 --> 01:12:02.877
Swim!

1347
01:12:07.506 --> 01:12:08.925
Ha-ha! Trenette!

1348
01:12:28.162 --> 01:12:29.414
Come on!

1349
01:12:32.375 --> 01:12:34.419
- Thank you.
- Don't thank me.

1350
01:12:35.586 --> 01:12:38.089
Stop crying and tag Guido! <i>Imbecille!</i>

1351
01:12:38.172 --> 01:12:39.006
<i>Andiamo!</i> Run. run!

1352
01:12:44.187 --> 01:12:45.188
<i>Finito!</i>

1353
01:12:50.735 --> 01:12:53.237
<i>Permille cavoli.</i> Guido! Faster!

1354
01:12:53.404 --> 01:12:55.198
Eat. <i>idiota! Più veloce!</i>

1355
01:12:55.281 --> 01:12:56.574
Hey. that's not allowed.

1356
01:12:56.657 --> 01:12:57.825
He's done!

1357
01:13:02.288 --> 01:13:03.498
Done!

1358
01:13:11.047 --> 01:13:12.048
Whoa.

1359
01:13:21.057 --> 01:13:22.475
But he's gotta be here somewhere.

1360
01:13:22.558 --> 01:13:24.143
Thirsty? Water. anyone?

1361
01:13:24.227 --> 01:13:25.394
- Please. don't!
- Not again!

1362
01:13:25.478 --> 01:13:27.230
That's him. That's him!

1363
01:13:27.313 --> 01:13:28.314
Luca. stop!

1364
01:13:29.941 --> 01:13:32.527
Sorry. Mom! Sorry. Dad! I have to do this!

1365
01:13:32.610 --> 01:13:35.613
Get back here right now!

1366
01:13:36.072 --> 01:13:38.074
Wow. He's fast.

1367
01:13:39.575 --> 01:13:41.202
What?

1368
01:13:47.959 --> 01:13:49.418
Oops! <i>Scusa.</i>

1369
01:13:49.502 --> 01:13:51.587
I'll catch you on the... downhill!

1370
01:13:51.671 --> 01:13:54.423
Spewlia. you never even
made it to the downhill.

1371
01:13:55.591 --> 01:13:57.301
What?

1372
01:13:59.637 --> 01:14:03.683
<i>Impossibile!</i> He's cheating!
<i>Arbitro! Arbitro!</i>

1373
01:14:04.684 --> 01:14:05.977
Huh?

1374
01:14:06.060 --> 01:14:07.103
No. no. no!

1375
01:14:12.525 --> 01:14:13.526
Ooh.

1376
01:14:21.993 --> 01:14:24.161
Oh. not now! Come on. come on!

1377
01:14:24.245 --> 01:14:25.997
I'm so close!

1378
01:14:28.082 --> 01:14:29.667
Luca!

1379
01:14:32.295 --> 01:14:33.462
Just stay right there!

1380
01:14:33.546 --> 01:14:34.547
Alberto.

1381
01:14:34.630 --> 01:14:35.965
I'm coming for you!

1382
01:14:36.591 --> 01:14:38.134
What's wrong. <i>piccoletto?</i>

1383
01:14:38.217 --> 01:14:39.886
Afraid of a little rain?

1384
01:14:39.969 --> 01:14:40.970
- Hey!
- Huh?

1385
01:14:41.721 --> 01:14:43.973
For the last time.
you two don't belong here.

1386
01:14:44.140 --> 01:14:45.850
Get out of my town!

1387
01:14:51.647 --> 01:14:54.025
Sea monster! Right there!

1388
01:14:54.108 --> 01:14:55.151
Huh?

1389
01:14:55.234 --> 01:14:56.319
<i>Mamma mia!</i>

1390
01:14:56.402 --> 01:14:58.571
Ciccio! My harpoon! <i>Veloce!</i>

1391
01:15:01.741 --> 01:15:04.744
- Alberto...
- No. stop! Just stay there.

1392
01:15:06.078 --> 01:15:07.204
You're still okay.

1393
01:15:07.830 --> 01:15:10.124
<i>- Andiamo!</i>
- Alberto. wait!

1394
01:15:13.711 --> 01:15:14.837
No!

1395
01:15:32.980 --> 01:15:34.148
What?

1396
01:15:34.482 --> 01:15:36.734
Whoa! You really are crazy!

1397
01:15:36.817 --> 01:15:38.569
Learned it from you!

1398
01:15:38.653 --> 01:15:40.154
Let's get to the water!

1399
01:15:41.405 --> 01:15:42.823
No! Ciccio!

1400
01:15:42.907 --> 01:15:43.908
Here it is.

1401
01:15:48.579 --> 01:15:50.206
Hey there.

1402
01:15:50.289 --> 01:15:51.457
Excuse us.

1403
01:15:51.540 --> 01:15:54.001
Out of the way! <i>Via. via!</i>

1404
01:16:03.970 --> 01:16:04.971
Ha-ha!

1405
01:16:08.140 --> 01:16:09.141
Luca!

1406
01:16:13.521 --> 01:16:15.523
Sorry!

1407
01:16:23.155 --> 01:16:24.699
- Oh. no! Luca!
- Son!

1408
01:16:27.243 --> 01:16:29.412
You should've left when I told you.

1409
01:16:29.495 --> 01:16:32.540
Now. I gotta kill some sea monsters!

1410
01:16:34.250 --> 01:16:36.919
So long. evil empire of injustice.

1411
01:16:41.632 --> 01:16:43.426
No!

1412
01:16:43.509 --> 01:16:44.760
Giulia!

1413
01:16:50.641 --> 01:16:52.935
<i>Mostri marini!</i> Give me that!

1414
01:16:55.067 --> 01:16:55.776
Giulia. Are you all right?

1415
01:16:55.860 --> 01:16:58.487
Yeah. Yeah. I'm... I'm okay.

1416
01:16:59.071 --> 01:17:00.573
Thanks. guys.

1417
01:17:01.365 --> 01:17:02.658
Giulietta?

1418
01:17:02.742 --> 01:17:03.909
<i>Papà!</i> I...

1419
01:17:07.079 --> 01:17:08.873
Look at that!

1420
01:17:08.956 --> 01:17:09.623
You're not going anywhere. Come on.

1421
01:17:10.473 --> 01:17:13.309
I saw them first! The reward is mine!

1422
01:17:13.851 --> 01:17:14.936
We're not afraid of you!

1423
01:17:15.019 --> 01:17:17.146
No. but we're afraid of you.

1424
01:17:17.230 --> 01:17:20.316
Everyone is horrified
and disgusted by you.

1425
01:17:20.400 --> 01:17:22.276
because you are monsters.

1426
01:17:22.360 --> 01:17:23.986
Stop! They are not monsters.

1427
01:17:24.070 --> 01:17:25.988
Oh. yeah? Who are they. then?

1428
01:17:26.072 --> 01:17:26.906
I know who they are.

1429
01:17:37.554 --> 01:17:40.265
They are Luca and Alberto.

1430
01:17:41.767 --> 01:17:42.643
and...

1431
01:17:43.747 --> 01:17:46.500
they are the winners.

1432
01:17:48.335 --> 01:17:50.295
- Luca!
- Let us through!

1433
01:17:50.379 --> 01:17:51.380
- What?
- Really?

1434
01:17:51.463 --> 01:17:53.674
They can't be the winners.
They are not even people!

1435
01:17:53.757 --> 01:17:55.092
<i>Signora</i> Marsigliese?

1436
01:17:56.760 --> 01:17:59.346
Technically. legally.

1437
01:17:59.847 --> 01:18:00.889
yes. they won.

1438
01:18:00.973 --> 01:18:02.516
We won?

1439
01:18:02.599 --> 01:18:04.726
Who cares if they won?
They are sea monsters.

1440
01:18:10.274 --> 01:18:12.401
- <i>Andiamo.</i>
- Hmm.

1441
01:18:15.612 --> 01:18:16.613
What? Come on!

1442
01:18:16.697 --> 01:18:17.698
- Hey!
- Ha!

1443
01:18:17.781 --> 01:18:19.491
Ciccio! Guido! Another harpoon.

1444
01:18:20.284 --> 01:18:24.037
Ah. <i>idioti!</i> Be useful for once
in your pathetic lives.

1445
01:18:24.663 --> 01:18:26.290
- Guido.
- Ciccio.

1446
01:18:30.586 --> 01:18:32.463
Oops.

1447
01:18:32.546 --> 01:18:34.798
No. <i>piccolino.</i>

1448
01:18:35.174 --> 01:18:37.134
It's over. the reign of terror.

1449
01:18:37.217 --> 01:18:38.677
It's finally over!

1450
01:18:39.602 --> 01:18:40.311
- Luca!
- Luca!

1451
01:18:41.687 --> 01:18:43.814
You had us worried half to death.
and you must never do that again!

1452
01:18:43.898 --> 01:18:44.899
I'm sorry.

1453
01:18:44.982 --> 01:18:47.902
And you raced your little tail off
and kicked so much human butt!

1454
01:18:47.985 --> 01:18:51.030
And I'm so proud of you.
and I am so mad at you!

1455
01:18:52.281 --> 01:18:53.657
I love you. Mom.

1456
01:18:53.824 --> 01:18:54.825
Son.

1457
01:18:59.204 --> 01:19:00.956
<i>Signore e signori.</i>

1458
01:19:01.040 --> 01:19:04.418
the winners of this year's Portorosso Cup.

1459
01:19:04.877 --> 01:19:06.170
the underdogs.

1460
01:19:06.253 --> 01:19:08.422
Wow.

1461
01:19:08.547 --> 01:19:10.257
- Wow.
- Yeah!

1462
01:19:10.841 --> 01:19:12.176
- I can't believe we won!
- We won!

1463
01:19:12.259 --> 01:19:13.636
Yes! Underdogs!

1464
01:19:13.719 --> 01:19:15.387
Ugh.

1465
01:19:21.435 --> 01:19:22.978
- Give me that!
- Here.

1466
01:19:29.777 --> 01:19:30.819
We did it!

1467
01:19:31.987 --> 01:19:33.113
They won!

1468
01:19:36.631 --> 01:19:38.925
Feast your eyes on the greatest Vespa

1469
01:19:39.008 --> 01:19:40.635
the world has ever seen!

1470
01:19:43.096 --> 01:19:44.639
Perfect.

1471
01:19:49.853 --> 01:19:50.895
Mmm.

1472
01:19:51.521 --> 01:19:53.398
- <i>Signora.
- Grazie.</i>

1473
01:19:53.481 --> 01:19:54.983
Mom! What are you doing here?

1474
01:19:55.066 --> 01:19:57.068
I come to town most weekends.

1475
01:19:58.278 --> 01:19:59.571
You're not gonna catch me!

1476
01:19:59.654 --> 01:20:01.364
- Underdogs forever!
- Whoo-hoo!

1477
01:20:01.447 --> 01:20:06.286
What he did today was amazing.

1478
01:20:06.369 --> 01:20:08.872
But we can't let him stay in this world.

1479
01:20:09.539 --> 01:20:10.540
Can we?

1480
01:20:10.623 --> 01:20:13.293
Some people. they'll never accept him.

1481
01:20:14.460 --> 01:20:16.170
But some will.

1482
01:20:16.254 --> 01:20:19.465
And he seems to know
how to find the good ones.

1483
01:20:22.927 --> 01:20:24.512
So. where will you go first?

1484
01:20:24.596 --> 01:20:26.431
We're gonna stick around here for a bit.

1485
01:20:26.514 --> 01:20:29.475
We gotta fix this thing up
before we take it across the entire Earth.

1486
01:20:29.559 --> 01:20:32.061
Okay. Just don't forget to pack.

1487
01:20:32.145 --> 01:20:35.565
<i>Santo Gorgonzola!</i>
I need to pack! For school!

1488
01:20:35.648 --> 01:20:39.694
Oh. yeah. school.
You're gonna learn so much.

1489
01:20:39.777 --> 01:20:42.113
Um. I can leave you some books.

1490
01:20:42.196 --> 01:20:43.406
You can?

1491
01:20:43.698 --> 01:20:45.325
Come on. Alberto!

1492
01:20:57.378 --> 01:20:59.213
And you have your lunch for the train?

1493
01:20:59.297 --> 01:21:01.591
<i>- Sì.</i>
- Sweater? If it gets cold?

1494
01:21:01.674 --> 01:21:04.093
For the millionth time. <i>sì.</i>

1495
01:21:04.177 --> 01:21:06.220
I love you. too. <i>Papà.</i>

1496
01:21:08.264 --> 01:21:10.850
<i>Santa mozzarella.</i> we did it.

1497
01:21:10.934 --> 01:21:13.269
Well. Giulia.
can't wait to race next summer.

1498
01:21:13.353 --> 01:21:15.438
Or we could just have fun.

1499
01:21:17.273 --> 01:21:18.566
<i>Ciao.</i> Giulia.

1500
01:21:29.035 --> 01:21:31.663
Well. let's go fix up our Vespa.

1501
01:21:31.746 --> 01:21:33.581
Yeah. about that. Uh...

1502
01:21:34.779 --> 01:21:36.197
It's a crazy thing. I might have sold it.

1503
01:21:39.701 --> 01:21:40.702
Luca?

1504
01:21:40.952 --> 01:21:43.538
Mom? What are you all doing here?

1505
01:21:44.998 --> 01:21:49.085
If you promise to write to us
every single day

1506
01:21:49.169 --> 01:21:52.380
and be as safe as possible.
and I mean safer than safe.

1507
01:21:55.067 --> 01:21:56.193
you can go to school.

1508
01:21:56.485 --> 01:21:57.737
I can?

1509
01:21:57.820 --> 01:21:59.405
It's all arranged. actually.

1510
01:21:59.488 --> 01:22:01.490
You'd stay with Giulia and her mom.

1511
01:22:01.574 --> 01:22:03.451
Your friend talked them into it.

1512
01:22:03.534 --> 01:22:04.827
It wasn't easy.

1513
01:22:07.121 --> 01:22:08.664
Luca. do you promise?

1514
01:22:08.748 --> 01:22:10.458
Yes! Yes. I promise!

1515
01:22:11.208 --> 01:22:12.418
Thank you.

1516
01:22:14.003 --> 01:22:17.590
Oh. Just remember.
we are always here for you.

1517
01:22:17.673 --> 01:22:18.674
Okay?

1518
01:22:19.508 --> 01:22:21.635
Hey. Look me in the eye.

1519
01:22:22.511 --> 01:22:24.388
You know I love you. right?

1520
01:22:24.472 --> 01:22:26.474
I know.

1521
01:22:31.979 --> 01:22:34.023
Come on. Alberto. The train's gonna leave.

1522
01:22:36.233 --> 01:22:37.735
Where's your stuff?

1523
01:22:38.527 --> 01:22:40.613
Yeah. well. you see...

1524
01:22:40.696 --> 01:22:42.198
You are coming. right?

1525
01:22:42.615 --> 01:22:46.911
Um. I would. but Massimo asked
if I wanted to stick around.

1526
01:22:46.994 --> 01:22:49.830
Move in maybe. And I just thought. uh...

1527
01:22:51.082 --> 01:22:53.709
I think he needs me.
You know?

1528
01:22:55.753 --> 01:22:57.755
I can't do it without you.

1529
01:22:57.838 --> 01:22:59.340
But you're never without me.

1530
01:23:01.967 --> 01:23:03.886
The next time that you jump off a cliff

1531
01:23:03.969 --> 01:23:06.639
or tell Bruno to quit bothering you.

1532
01:23:07.014 --> 01:23:08.265
that's me.

1533
01:23:09.058 --> 01:23:12.269
But how am I gonna know you're okay?

1534
01:23:20.194 --> 01:23:22.029
You got me off the island. Luca.

1535
01:23:24.365 --> 01:23:25.408
I'm okay.

1536
01:23:34.458 --> 01:23:37.711
Seriously.
what does that mean?

1537
01:23:37.878 --> 01:23:40.423
No idea. Go find out for me. will ya?

1538
01:23:50.599 --> 01:23:52.560
Go. Luca!

1539
01:23:52.643 --> 01:23:54.228
Go!

1540
01:23:54.311 --> 01:23:57.273
Yeah! Whoo-hoo!

1541
01:33:48.359 --> 01:33:51.237
Some people think
I'm mad to live in the deep.

1542
01:33:51.654 --> 01:33:54.365
I think that they are the ones
who are mad.

1543
01:33:54.448 --> 01:33:57.076
not me the one who is mad. it's them.

1544
01:33:57.243 --> 01:33:59.328
It's a nice life. simple life.

1545
01:33:59.495 --> 01:34:01.414
It's away from the hustle and bustle.

1546
01:34:01.497 --> 01:34:03.124
all the stuff that you don't want.

1547
01:34:05.751 --> 01:34:08.004
Mmm. Whale carcass.

1548
01:34:08.754 --> 01:34:10.214
Anyway. you're gonna have fun.

1549
01:34:10.506 --> 01:34:13.926
You'll get to hear me talk.
I can talk without stopping.

1550
01:34:14.010 --> 01:34:17.179
sometimes for maybe 12 hours.

1551
01:34:17.555 --> 01:34:19.974
And you get to listen. so you're lucky.

1552
01:34:21.517 --> 01:34:23.019
Well done.

1552
01:34:24.305 --> 01:35:24.623
Do you want subtitles for any video?
